River Gate","New Road and River Port","Island","Genly's Lodgings"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"The capital city of Karhide, known for its grand architecture and political significance. A monumental structure completed to enhance Erhenrang's trade and infrastructure. A communal living space for foreigners in Erhenrang, where Genly Ai resides.","recentEvents":"Hosted a parade celebrating the completion of the Arch of the River Gate, where Genly Ai interacts with key figures like King Argaven XV and Therem Harth rem ir Estraven.; Central to the parade, with the king and masons participating in its final assembly.; Where Genly Ai reflects on his isolation and observes local customs.","relationships":[{"location":"Royal House","relationship":"Contains the royal residence and administrative center"},{"location":"Palace of Erhenrang","relationship":"Part of the city's walled inner complex"}]},{"name":"Royal House","aliases":["King's Residence","Royal Palace"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"The fortified palace complex housing the king and key political figures.","recentEvents":"Served as the backdrop for the royal procession and the keystone-laying ceremony.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Central structure within the city"},{"location":"King's House","relationship":"Part of the same complex"}]},{"name":"Corner Red Dwelling","aliases":["Estraven's Home"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"A historic residence of Therem Harth rem ir Estraven, symbolizing his political influence.","recentEvents":"Where Genly Ai is invited for dinner, revealing shifting power dynamics.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Located within the city's walls"}]},{"name":"Winter","aliases":["Planet Winter","Gethen"],"description":"The icy planet where Karhide is located, with extreme seasonal variations.","recentEvents":"Setting for the entire narrative, with Genly Ai navigating its harsh climate and politics.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Nation on the planet"}]},{"name":"Old Bridge","aliases":["Ancient Bridge"],"description":"A historic bridge over the river, noted for its arches and traditional construction methods.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a reference point for the arch's mortar techniques.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Historical structure in the city"}]},{"name":"Sess Embankment","aliases":["River Embankment"],"description":"A public area along the river where crowds gather for events.","recentEvents":"Where the parade crowd watches the keystone ceremony and the king's procession.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Key public space in the city"}],"parentLocation":"Erhenrang"},{"name":"Karhide","aliases":["Nation of Karhide"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"A politically complex nation on Winter, ruled by King Argaven XV.","recentEvents":"Central to the narrative, with Genly Ai navigating its social and political structures.","relationships":[{"location":"Winter","relationship":"Nation on the planet"}]},{"name":"North Fall","aliases":["High North Fall"],"description":"A remote, snowbound region bordering Karhide and Orgoreyn, marked by harsh climate and political tension.","recentEvents":"Estraven discusses aiding Karhidish farmers displaced from the Sinoth Valley, risking political fallout with the king.","relationships":[{"location":"Sassinoth Valley","relationship":"Adjacent border region contested by Karhide and Orgoreyn"},{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of Karhide's northern territory"}]},{"name":"Sassinoth Valley","aliases":["Sinoth Valley"],"arc":"Estraven's Political Maneuvering and Border Dispute (Historical Context)","description":"A disputed valley in the North Fall claimed by Karhide but inhabited by Orgoreyn settlers for millennia.","recentEvents":"Estraven's efforts to relocate farmers from the valley escalate tensions between Karhide and Orgoreyn.","relationships":[{"location":"North Fall","relationship":"Part of the contested border region"},{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Historically inhabited by Orgoreyn settlers"}]},{"name":"Remny Tower","description":"A tower in Erhenrang where gongs mark the time, symbolizing the city's rigid temporal structure.","recentEvents":"Estraven and Genly Ai hear the gongs signaling midnight as their conversation concludes.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Part of the city's infrastructure"}]},{"name":"Pering Storm-border","aliases":["Storm-border"],"description":"A region in northern Karhide bordering the Pering Ice, known for its harsh climate and the tragic tale of Getheren and Hode.","recentEvents":"The brothers Getheren and Hode vowed kemmering, but their vow was broken after Getheren's brother committed suicide, leading Getheren to flee northward.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Adjacent region"},{"location":"Shath Domain","relationship":"Historical location tied to the brothers' story"}]},{"name":"Pering Ice","aliases":["Pering Glacier"],"description":"A vast glacial sheet covering northern Karhide, contiguous with the Gobrin Ice of Orgoreyn during winter.","recentEvents":"Getheren traveled northward across the Ice, encountering a supernatural realm where the dead dwell.","relationships":[{"location":"Gobrin Ice","relationship":"Contiguous during winter"},{"location":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","relationship":"Site of Getheren's encounter with Hode"}]},{"name":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","aliases":["Blizzard Place"],"description":"A supernatural realm existing within the Pering Ice, where the dead who died in kemmering dwell eternally.","recentEvents":"Getheren met his deceased brother Hode here, who could not speak his name due to his death.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Located within the glacier"},{"location":"Shath Domain","relationship":"Linked to the brothers' tragic history"}]},{"name":"Gobrin Ice","description":"A glacial expanse in Orgoreyn, contiguous with the Pering Ice during winter storms.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a geographical counterpart to the Pering Ice, part of the frozen north.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Contiguous during winter"}]},{"name":"Shath Domain","aliases":["Hearth of Shath"],"description":"A Karhidish domain where the tragic tale of Getheren and Hode originated.","recentEvents":"The brothers' broken vow and Getheren's exile began here, leading to his journey north.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Storm-border","relationship":"Historical location tied to the brothers' story"}]},{"name":"Orgoreyn","aliases":["Karhide's neighbor"],"description":"A rival state to Karhide, known for its harsh environment and political tensions.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai contemplates traveling here but hesitates due to potential difficulties returning to Karhide.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Adjacent rival state"}]},{"name":"Fastnesses","arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"A remote eastern region of Karhide containing the Foretellers, who hold significant cultural and prophetic influence.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai resolves to travel here to gather information about Karhide's political dynamics.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Eastern region"}]},{"name":"Grende","aliases":["Grende Region"],"description":"A region in northern Osnoriner, home to Charuthe.","recentEvents":"Herbor travels through the snows of Grende on his way to Charuthe to seek a foretelling for Berosty rem ir Ipe.","relationships":[{"location":"Charuthe","relationship":"Adjacent region"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","status":"active","characters":["Genly Ai","King Argaven XV","Therem Harth rem ir Estraven"],"summary":"Ai resolves to l