ip":"Part of the contested border region"},{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Historically inhabited by Orgoreyn settlers"},{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Site of political resistance to the Envoy's mission"}]},{"name":"Remny Tower","description":"A tower in Erhenrang where gongs mark the time, symbolizing the city's rigid temporal structure.","recentEvents":"Estraven and Genly Ai hear the gongs signaling midnight as their conversation concludes.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Part of the city's infrastructure"}]},{"name":"Pering Storm-border","aliases":["Storm-border"],"description":"A region in northern Karhide bordering the Pering Ice, known for its harsh climate and the tragic tale of Getheren and Hode.","recentEvents":"The brothers Getheren and Hode vowed kemmering, but their vow was broken after Getheren's brother committed suicide, leading Getheren to flee northward.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Adjacent region"},{"location":"Shath Domain","relationship":"Historical location tied to the brothers' story"}]},{"name":"Pering Ice","aliases":["Pering Glacier"],"description":"A vast glacial sheet covering northern Karhide, contiguous with the Gobrin Ice of Orgoreyn during winter.","recentEvents":"Getheren traveled northward across the Ice, encountering a supernatural realm where the dead dwell.","relationships":[{"location":"Gobrin Ice","relationship":"Contiguous during winter"},{"location":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","relationship":"Site of Getheren's encounter with Hode"}]},{"name":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","aliases":["Blizzard Place"],"description":"A supernatural realm existing within the Pering Ice, where the dead who died in kemmering dwell eternally.","recentEvents":"Getheren met his deceased brother Hode here, who could not speak his name due to his death.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Located within the glacier"},{"location":"Shath Domain","relationship":"Linked to the brothers' tragic history"}]},{"name":"Gobrin Ice","description":"A glacial expanse in Orgoreyn, contiguous with the Pering Ice during winter storms.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a geographical counterpart to the Pering Ice, part of the frozen north.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Contiguous during winter"}]},{"name":"Shath Domain","aliases":["Hearth of Shath"],"description":"A Karhidish domain where the tragic tale of Getheren and Hode originated.","recentEvents":"The brothers' broken vow and Getheren's exile began here, leading to his journey north.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Storm-border","relationship":"Historical location tied to the brothers' story"}]},{"name":"Orgoreyn","aliases":["Karhide's neighbor"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"A rival state to Karhide, known for its harsh environment and political tensions.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai contemplates traveling here but hesitates due to potential difficulties returning to Karhide.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Adjacent rival state"}]},{"name":"Fastnesses","arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"A remote eastern region of Karhide containing the Foretellers, who hold significant cultural and prophetic influence.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai resolves to travel here to gather information about Karhide's political dynamics.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Eastern region"}]},{"name":"Grende","aliases":["Grende Region"],"description":"A region in northern Osnoriner, home to Charuthe.","recentEvents":"Herbor travels through the snows of Grende on his way to Charuthe to seek a foretelling for Berosty rem ir Ipe.","relationships":[{"location":"Charuthe","relationship":"Adjacent region"}]},{"name":"New Port","aliases":["New Port"],"description":"A coastal city serving as a departure point for caravans heading east.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai departs from here aboard a trade-caravan bound for the Pering Storm-border.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Storm-border","relationship":"Part of the caravan's route"}]},{"name":"Eskar Pass","aliases":["Eskar Pass"],"description":"A mountain pass through the Kargav range, critical for caravan travel.","recentEvents":"The caravan traverses this pass, encountering extreme weather and avalanches.","relationships":[{"location":"Kargav","relationship":"A key route through the mountain range"}]},{"name":"Ariskostor Fastness","aliases":["Ariskostor Fastness"],"description":"A remote castle-like structure perched on the Kargav's southern face.","recentEvents":"The driver describes it as a residence for the Old Men, inaccessible for most of the year.","relationships":[{"location":"Kargav","relationship":"Located on the mountain range"}]},{"name":"Otherhord","aliases":["Otherhord"],"arc":"Gethenian Cultural Exploration","description":"A secluded Fastness in a forested region, home to the Handdara cult.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai stays here to study the Foretellers' practices and their philosophy of nusuth.","relationships":[{"location":"Fastnesses","relationship":"A specific example of a Handdara retreat"}]},{"name":"Spreve","description":"Domain of the physician from Spreve, a region known for its medical expertise and connection to the Foretellers.","recentEvents":"The physician from Spreve entered the Foretelling circle during the session, interrupting the ritual with a demand for light.","relationships":[{"location":"Otherhord","relationship":"The physician's origin domain"}]},{"name":"Kuseben","aliases":["Kuseben"],"description":"A coastal town in Karhide where Estraven meets Ashe and attempts to flee exile.","recentEvents":"Estraven arrives in Kuseben after fleeing Erhenrang, meets Ashe, and tries to escape to Orgoreyn by sea.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Bordering region; Estraven's escape route"}]},{"name":"Shelt Port","aliases":["Shelt"],"description":"A port city in Orgoreyn where Estraven is set ashore after being intercepted by patrol.","recentEvents":"Estraven is rescued by the Kuseben Patrol and landed here, leading to his detention in the Commensal Hospital.","relationships":[{"location":"Charisune Coastal Area Four","relationship":"Adjacent coastal region"}]},{"name":"Markets of South Mishnory","aliases":["South Mishnory Markets"],"description":"A bustling market hub in Mishnory where Estraven finds work as a landboat loader.","recentEvents":"Estraven works in the ice-houses and lodges on Fish Island, navigating Orgoreyn's social and political systems.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Central commercial district"}]},{"name":"Fish Island","aliases":["Fish Island"],"description":"A crowded island near Mishnory's Markets where Estraven lodges with fellow workers.","recentEvents":"Estraven resides here while working in the ice-houses, enduring harsh conditions and social scrutiny.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Residential district"}]},{"name":"Kunderer Embankment","aliases":["Kunderer Embankment"],"description":"A tree-lined area in Mishnory offering respite from the city's heat.","recentEvents":"Estraven retreats here to escape the oppressive summer heat of Mishnory.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Recreational area"}]},{"name":"Charisune Coastal Area Four","aliases":["Charisune Coastal Area Four"],"description":"A coastal region in Orgoreyn housing the Commensal Hospital where Estraven is detained.","recentEvents":"Estraven is hospitalized here after a failed escape attempt, where he encounters the Inspector and physician.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Administrative district"}]},{"name":"Sennethny","aliases":["Sennethny"],"description":"A location within the Twenty-fourth Commensality of Orgoreyn, tied to Estraven's hospital stay.","recentEvents":"Estraven is registered as a dependent in this commensality after his hospitalization.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Subdivision of the Great Commensality"}]},{"name":"Osnoriner","aliases":["Osnoriner Region"],"description":"A region in Karhide known for its unique divorce practices and social customs.","recentEvents":"Discussed as a place where divorce exists but remarriage after divorce or death is prohibited.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of the Karhide region"}]},{"name":"Perunter","aliases":["Perunter Continent"],"description":"An Antarctic continent where incest between generations is reportedly permitted, though disputed.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a possible location with different social norms regarding incest.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Adjacent or nearby region"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","status":"active","characters":["Genly Ai","Therem Harth rem ir Estraven"],"summary":"Ai's request to enter Orgoreyn and the political discussions with Estraven highlight the risks and potential for alliance between Karhide and Orgoreyn."},{"name":"Estraven's Exile and Cross-National Political Struggles","status":"active","characters":["Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","Commensal Yegey","Commensal Obsle"],"summary":"Estraven navigates political tensions by advocating for the Envoy's mission, emphasizing the need to address the greater challenge beyond Karhide and Orgoreyn."},{"name":"Gethenian Cultural Exploration","status":"active","characters":["Genly Ai","Weaver Odren","Faxe the Weaver"],"summary":"Ai immerses himself in the Handdara cult's practices at Otherhord, observing the Foretellers' enigmatic rituals and the philosophy of nusuth, deepening his understanding of Gethenian culture and its contrast to Terran norms."}],"summary":"Genly Ai and Estraven continue their journey across Gethen, navigating political tensions between Karhide and Orgoreyn. The chapter delves into Gethenian biology, detailing the somer-kemmer cycle and societal structures shaped by ambisexuality. Key themes include the absence of traditional gender roles, the lack of war, and the cultural significance of the cold environment. The narrative remains focused on the protagonists' search for the Gheredan and the broader implications of Gethenian society."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":11,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Genly Ai","aliases":["Mr. Ai","the Envoy"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"8. Another Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"The Ekumen's Envoy to Karhide, struggling with the political and psychological complexities of his mission.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Former contact; Estraven is now the King’s Ear"},{"character":"King Argaven XV","relationship":"The monarch he is attempting to persuade to join the Ekumen"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived in Mishnory, met with Commissioner Shusgis, and encountered Lord Estraven at a supper party."},{"name":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","aliases":["The King’s Ear","Lord Estraven"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"8. Another Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"The king's trusted advisor exiled for allegedly conspiring to undermine Karhide's sovereignty.","relationships":[{"character":"King Argaven XV","relationship":"Formerly the king's closest confidant and advisor"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Allied through covert communication and financial support"},{"character":"Foreth rem ir Osboth","relationship":"Former kemmering (male companion)"}],"recentEvents":"Received a message and funds from Foreth rem ir Osboth, met Genly Ai at a supper party."},{"name":"King Argaven XV","aliases":["the king"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Royal House","description":"The paranoid and volatile ruler of Karhide, suspicious of forei