}]},{"name":"Remny Tower","description":"A tower in Erhenrang where gongs mark the time, symbolizing the city's rigid temporal structure.","recentEvents":"Estraven and Genly Ai hear the gongs signaling midnight as their conversation concludes.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Part of the city's infrastructure"}]},{"name":"Pering Storm-border","aliases":["Storm-border"],"description":"A region in northern Karhide bordering the Pering Ice, known for its harsh climate and the tragic tale of Getheren and Hode.","recentEvents":"The brothers Getheren and Hode vowed kemmering, but their vow was broken after Getheren's brother committed suicide, leading Getheren to flee northward.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Adjacent region"},{"location":"Shath Domain","relationship":"Historical location tied to the brothers' story"}]},{"name":"Pering Ice","aliases":["Pering Glacier"],"description":"A vast glacial sheet covering northern Karhide, contiguous with the Gobrin Ice of Orgoreyn during winter.","recentEvents":"Getheren traveled northward across the Ice, encountering a supernatural realm where the dead dwell.","relationships":[{"location":"Gobrin Ice","relationship":"Contiguous during winter"},{"location":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","relationship":"Site of Getheren's encounter with Hode"}]},{"name":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","aliases":["Blizzard Place"],"description":"A supernatural realm existing within the Pering Ice, where the dead who died in kemmering dwell eternally.","recentEvents":"Getheren met his deceased brother Hode here, who could not speak his name due to his death.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Located within the glacier"},{"location":"Shath Domain","relationship":"Linked to the brothers' tragic history"}]},{"name":"Gobrin Ice","description":"A glacial expanse in Orgoreyn, contiguous with the Pering Ice during winter storms.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a geographical counterpart to the Pering Ice, part of the frozen north.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Contiguous during winter"}]},{"name":"Shath Domain","aliases":["Hearth of Shath"],"description":"A Karhidish domain where the tragic tale of Getheren and Hode originated.","recentEvents":"The brothers' broken vow and Getheren's exile began here, leading to his journey north.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Storm-border","relationship":"Historical location tied to the brothers' story"}]},{"name":"Orgoreyn","aliases":["Karhide's neighbor"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Orgoreyn Political Tensions","description":"A rival state to Karhide, known for its harsh environment and political tensions.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai contemplates traveling here but hesitates due to potential difficulties returning to Karhide.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Adjacent rival state"}]},{"name":"Fastnesses","arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"A remote eastern region of Karhide containing the Foretellers, who hold significant cultural and prophetic influence.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai resolves to travel here to gather information about Karhide's political dynamics.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Eastern region"}]},{"name":"Grende","aliases":["Grende Region"],"description":"A region in northern Osnoriner, home to Charuthe.","recentEvents":"Herbor travels through the snows of Grende on his way to Charuthe to seek a foretelling for Berosty rem ir Ipe.","relationships":[{"location":"Charuthe","relationship":"Adjacent region"}]},{"name":"New Port","aliases":["New Port"],"description":"A coastal city serving as a departure point for caravans heading east.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai departs from here aboard a trade-caravan bound for the Pering Storm-border.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Storm-border","relationship":"Part of the caravan's route"}]},{"name":"Eskar Pass","aliases":["Eskar Pass"],"description":"A mountain pass through the Kargav range, critical for caravan travel.","recentEvents":"The caravan traverses this pass, encountering extreme weather and avalanches.","relationships":[{"location":"Kargav","relationship":"A key route through the mountain range"}]},{"name":"Ariskostor Fastness","aliases":["Ariskostor Fastness"],"description":"A remote castle-like structure perched on the Kargav's southern face.","recentEvents":"The driver describes it as a residence for the Old Men, inaccessible for most of the year.","relationships":[{"location":"Kargav","relationship":"Located on the mountain range"}]},{"name":"Otherhord","aliases":["Otherhord"],"arc":"Gethenian Cultural Exploration","description":"A secluded Fastness in a forested region, home to the Handdara cult.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai stays here to study the Foretellers' practices and their philosophy of nusuth.","relationships":[{"location":"Fastnesses","relationship":"A specific example of a Handdara retreat"}]},{"name":"Spreve","description":"Domain of the physician from Spreve, a region known for its medical expertise and connection to the Foretellers.","recentEvents":"The physician from Spreve entered the Foretelling circle during the session, interrupting the ritual with a demand for light.","relationships":[{"location":"Otherhord","relationship":"The physician's origin domain"}]},{"name":"Kuseben","aliases":["Kuseben"],"description":"A coastal town in Karhide where Estraven meets Ashe and attempts to flee exile.","recentEvents":"Estraven arrives in Kuseben after fleeing Erhenrang, meets Ashe, and tries to escape to Orgoreyn by sea.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Bordering region; Estraven's escape route"}]},{"name":"Shelt Port","aliases":["Shelt"],"description":"A port city in Orgoreyn where Estraven is set ashore after being intercepted by patrol.","recentEvents":"Estraven is rescued by the Kuseben Patrol and landed here, leading to his detention in the Commensal Hospital.","relationships":[{"location":"Charisune Coastal Area Four","relationship":"Adjacent coastal region"}]},{"name":"Markets of South Mishnory","aliases":["South Mishnory Markets"],"description":"A bustling market hub in Mishnory where Estraven finds work as a landboat loader.","recentEvents":"Estraven works in the ice-houses and lodges on Fish Island, navigating Orgoreyn's social and political systems.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Central commercial district"}]},{"name":"Fish Island","aliases":["Fish Island"],"description":"A crowded island near Mishnory's Markets where Estraven lodges with fellow workers.","recentEvents":"Estraven resides here while working in the ice-houses, enduring harsh conditions and social scrutiny.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Residential district"}]},{"name":"Kunderer Embankment","aliases":["Kunderer Embankment"],"description":"A tree-lined area in Mishnory offering respite from the city's heat.","recentEvents":"Estraven retreats here to escape the oppressive summer heat of Mishnory.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Recreational area"}]},{"name":"Charisune Coastal Area Four","aliases":["Charisune Coastal Area Four"],"description":"A coastal region in Orgoreyn housing the Commensal Hospital where Estraven is detained.","recentEvents":"Estraven is hospitalized here after a failed escape attempt, where he encounters the Inspector and physician.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Administrative district"}]},{"name":"Sennethny","aliases":["Sennethny"],"description":"A location within the Twenty-fourth Commensality of Orgoreyn, tied to Estraven's hospital stay.","recentEvents":"Estraven is registered as a dependent in this commensality after his hospitalization.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Subdivision of the Great Commensality"}]},{"name":"Osnoriner","aliases":["Osnoriner Region"],"description":"A region in Karhide known for its unique divorce practices and social customs.","recentEvents":"Discussed as a place where divorce exists but remarriage after divorce or death is prohibited.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of the Karhide region"}]},{"name":"Perunter","aliases":["Perunter Continent"],"description":"An Antarctic continent where incest between generations is reportedly permitted, though disputed.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a possible location with different social norms regarding incest.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Adjacent or nearby region"}]},{"name":"Gorinhering","aliases":["Gorinhering Clan-Hearth"],"description":"A Clan-Hearth on Karhide's Eastern coast, built on a hill above the Hodomin Ocean.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai resided here during the summer, interacting with locals and observing Karhidish culture.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of the Eastern coastal region"},{"location":"Hodomin Ocean","relationship":"Surrounded by the eternal fogs of this ocean"}]},{"name":"Ey River","description":"A glacier-fed border river between Karhide and Orgoreyn, marked by a bridge connecting Passerer and Siuwensin.","recentEvents":"A Karhidish foray raided Siuwensin, prompting Genly's journey into Orgoreyn.","relationships":[{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Karhidish village across the river"},{"location":"Siuwensin","relationship":"Orgota village across the river"}]},{"name":"Passerer","description":"A Karhidish village on the Karhide side of the Ey River bridge.","recentEvents":"A foray from Passerer raids Siuwensin, causing widespread destruction.","relationships":[{"location":"Ey River","relationship":"Located across the river from Siuwensin"},{"location":"Ovord Domain","relationship":"Alleged origin of foray guns"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent Commensal territory"}]},{"name":"Siuwensin","description":"An Orgota village on the Orgoreyn side of the Ey River bridge.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai and refugees are detained here after a raid, interrogated, and held in a storage-barn overnight.","relationships":[{"location":"Ey River","relationship":"Located across the river from Passerer"},{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Source of the raiding foray"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent inspection point"}],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Orgoreyn Political Tensions"},{"name":"Commensal Border-Station","description":"An Orgote border checkpoint where Genly obtained a permiso for travel.","recentEvents":"Processed Genly's entry into Orgoreyn after verifying his credentials.","relationships":[{"location":"Siuwensin","relationship":"Adjacent to the Commensal Transient-House"}]},{"name":"Ovord Domain","aliases":["Ovord Domain"],"description":"A Commensal region accused of supplying foray guns to Passerer.","recentEvents":"Whispers suggest Ovord Domain's involvement in the Siuwensin raid via foray guns.","relationships":[{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Alleged supplier of foray weapons"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent Commensal territory"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Genly Ai's Mission and Orgoreyn Political Tensions","status":"active","characters":["Genly Ai","King Argaven XV","Pemmer Harge rem ir Tibe"],"summary":"Ai arrives in Mishnory after navigating Orgote bureaucracy, now confronting political tensions between Karhide and Orgoreyn. His mission continues as he interacts with Orgote officials and learns of the raid on Siuwensin."},{"name":"Estraven's Exile and Cross-National Political Struggles","status":"active","characters":["Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","Foreth rem ir Osboth"],"summary":"Estraven's presence in Mishnory and the delivery of Foreth's money highlight his ongoing struggle for survival and political influence. His connection to the raid on Siuwensin underscores his role in the Karhide-Orgoreyn conflict."},{"name":"Gethenian Cultural Exploration","status":"active","characters":["Genly Ai","Commensal Slose","Commensal Obsle"],"summary":"Ai's observations of Orgote culture deepen as he interacts with Commensals, contrasting their structured society with Karhide's clan-based systems. The cultural exchange continues through conversations about Gethen's environment and philosophy."}],"summary":"Genly Ai continues his journey to Mishnory, passing through Siuwensin which was recently raided by a foray from Passerer. Refugees are detained and interrogated, while Genly is treated as a distinguished guest by Orgota authorities. He reflects on the political tensions between Commensal regions and the stark contrast between Karhide's chaos and Orgoreyn's bureaucratic order. His meeting with Commissioner Shusgis marks a pivotal moment in his mission to engage with Gethen's political landscape."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":12,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Genly Ai","aliases":["Mr. Ai","the Envoy"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"8. Another Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"The Ekumen's Envoy to Karhide, struggling with the political and psychological complexities of his mission.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Former contact; Estraven is now the King’s Ear"},{"character":"King Argaven XV","relationship":"The monarch he is attempting to persuade to join the Ekumen"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived in Mishnory, met with Commissioner Shusgis, and encountered Lord Estraven at a supper party."},{"name":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","aliases":["The King’s Ear","Lord Estraven"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A nobleman from the Domain of Estre, known for his complex relationship with Genly Ai and his role in ending the feud between Estre and Stok.","relationships":[{"character":"King Argaven XV","relationship":"Formerly the king's closest confidant and advisor"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Allied through covert communication and financial support"},{"character":"Foreth rem ir Osboth","relationship":"Former kemmering (male companion)"}],"recentEvents":"Saved the heir of Estre from death, later became Lord of Estre after his father's death, and was called 'Estraven the Traitor' for ending the feud."},{"name":"King Argaven XV","aliases":["the king"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Royal House","description":"The paranoid and volatile ruler of Karhide, suspicious of foreign influence and internal dissent.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Formerly his most trusted advisor, now exiled"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"The Envoy whose mission he resists and interrogates"}],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of Karhide’s political climate"},{"name":"Pemmer Harge rem ir Tibe","aliases":["the king’s cousin"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The king’s cousin and a member of the upper chamber, known for his rivalry with Estraven.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Rival and political adversary"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Interacted during the dinner conversation"}],"recentEvents":"Featured in news about Karhide’s territorial claims in the Sinoth Valley"},{"name":"servant","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"1. A Parade in Erhenrang","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Karhidish servant who left after the meal.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Departed to their home after the meal, as Karhiders do not employ bonded labor."},{"name":"Getheren","aliases":["Ennoch"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Brother who survived the exile and journey to the Ice, met his brother Hode in the Place Inside the Blizzard.","relationships":[{"character":"Hode","relationship":"Brother"}],"recentEvents":"Traveled to the Pering Ice, encountered Hode, died after returning to Shath and revealing his identity."},{"name":"Hode","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","description":"Getheren's brother who committed suicide after being exiled, now resides in the Place Inside the Blizzard.","relationships":[{"character":"Getheren","relationship":"Brother"}],"recentEvents":"Died by suicide, appeared to Getheren in the Place Inside the Blizzard as a white, lifeless figure."},{"name":"the traveler","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Carried Getheren's message back to Shath, confirming the domain's recovery after Getheren's death.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received Getheren's final message and relayed it to Shath, contributing to the domain's restoration."},{"name":"Lord Berosty rem ir Ipe","aliases":["Ashe Berosty rem ir Ipe"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"4. The Nineteenth Day","currentLocation":"Grende","description":"A nobleman who sought a Foretelling about his death and later killed his kemmering Herbor before dying by suicide.","relationships":[{"character":"Herbor of the Geganner clan","relationship":"kemmering"}],"recentEvents":"Received a Foretelling about his death, killed Herbor, and hanged himself on Odstreth."},{"name":"Herbor of the Geganner clan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"4. The Nineteenth Day","currentLocation":"Grende","description":"A poor man who sought a Foretelling to save his kemmering Berosty rem ir Ipe.","relationships":[{"character":"Lord Berosty rem ir Ipe","relationship":"kemmering"}],"recentEvents":"Sought a Foretelling, was killed by Berosty, and died from the injury."},{"name":"Weaver Odren","aliases":["The Weaver","the Weaver","Faxe"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Otherhord","description":"A Foreteller and the Weaver of the group, known for his role in the Foretelling sessions.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Envoy and seeker of answers"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted the Foretelling session for Genly Ai, where he answered the question about Gethen's membership in the Ekumen."},{"name":"Goss","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Otherhord","description":"A young Indweller who guides Genly Ai to the Fastness of Otherhord.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Guide and companion"}],"recentEvents":"Led Genly Ai to Otherhord and engaged in conversation about the Handdara"},{"name":"the driver","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"on the caravan","description":"The driver of the landboats guiding the caravan through the Kargav.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Guided the caravan and shared stories about the Fastnesses"},{"name":"the physician from Spreve","aliases":["the physician"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Otherhord","description":"A physician from Spreve who entered the circle during the Foretelling session.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Entered the circle during the Foretelling session, contributing to the disruption of the session."},{"name":"the cook","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"6. One Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A servant who wakes Therem Harth","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Helped Therem escape by providing food"},{"name":"the fisherman","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"6. One Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A fisherman who initially refused to help Therem","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Refused to assist Therem but later led to his capture"},{"name":"the Inspector","aliases":["Inspector"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"8. Another Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Commensal Border-Station","description":"A government official handling refugee interrogations and border controls.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Conducted thorough inspection of Genly Ai's passport and issued a permiso for Siuwensin."},{"name":"Commensal Yegey","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"8. Another Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A Commensal official involved in regional governance.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Former colleague"}],"recentEvents":"Attended a supper party with Genly Ai and other officials."},{"name":"Commensal Obsle","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"8. Another Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A Commensal official with an inquisitive nature.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Political associate"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged Genly Ai in conversation about off-world environments during a supper party."},{"name":"Foreth rem ir Osboth","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"8. Another Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Orgny Fastness","description":"Estraven's former kemmering, now an Indweller at Orgny Fastness.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Debt owed for aiding Estraven"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Genly Ai money to deliver to Estraven, expressing hope for his survival."},{"name":"the baby","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"8. Another Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"","relationships":[]},{"name":"Arek of Estre","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The heir of the Domain of Estre, who was killed by a Stok warrior during a feud between the two domains.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Killed by a Stok warrior while traveling through the thore-forest, his body left to be eaten by wild beasts."},{"name":"The murderer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Stok warrior who killed Arek of Estre during the feud between the domains.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Stabbed Arek of Estre to death and left his body to be eaten by wild beasts."},{"name":"The men from Stok","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A group of Stok warriors who disobeyed their lord's orders and left Arek of Estre's body to be eaten by wild beasts.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Disobeyed their lord's command to bury Arek of Estre, leading to their banishment."},{"name":"Lord Sorve","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The lord of the Domain of Estre who died, leaving his heir Therem to inherit the domain.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Died, leading to Therem becoming Lord of Estre and ending the feud with Stok."},{"name":"The old lord","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Estre","description":"The lord of the Domain of Estre who adopted the child of Arek of Estre as his heir.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Adopted the child of Arek of Estre and named him Therem, who later became Lord of Estre."},{"name":"The people from Ebos village","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Residents of Ebos village who helped Therem of Stok after he was wounded.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Carried Therem of Stok back to Estre after he was wounded in the thore-forest."}],"locations":[{"name":"Erhenrang","aliases":["Capital City","City of Karhide","Arch of the River Gate","New Road and River Port","Island","Genly's Lodgings"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"The capital city of Karhide, known for its grand architecture and political significance. A monumental structure completed to enhance Erhenrang's trade and infrastructure. A communal living space for foreigners in Erhenrang, where Genly Ai resides.","recentEvents":"Hosted a parade celebrating the completion of the Arch of the River Gate, where Genly Ai interacts with key figures like King Argaven XV and Therem Harth rem ir Estraven.; Central to the parade, with the king and masons participating in its final assembly.; Where Genly Ai reflects on his isolation and observes local customs.","relationships":[{"location":"Royal House","relationship":"Contains the royal residence and administrative center"},{"location":"Palace of Erhenrang","relationship":"Part of the city's walled inner complex"}]},{"name":"Royal House","aliases":["King's Residence","Royal Palace"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Orgoreyn Political Tensions","description":"The fortified palace complex housing the king and key political figures.","recentEvents":"Served as the backdrop for the royal procession and the keystone-laying ceremony.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Central structure within the city"},{"location":"King's House","relationship":"Part of the same complex"}]},{"name":"Corner Red Dwelling","aliases":["Estraven's Home"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"A historic residence of Therem Harth rem ir Estraven, symbolizing his political influence.","recentEvents":"Where Genly Ai is invited for dinner, revealing shifting power dynamics.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Located within the city's walls"}]},{"name":"Winter","aliases":["Planet Winter","Gethen"],"description":"The icy planet where Karhide is located, with extreme seasonal variations.","recentEvents":"Setting for the entire narrative, with Genly Ai navigating its harsh climate and politics.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Nation on the planet"}]},{"name":"Old Bridge","aliases":["Ancient Bridge"],"description":"A historic bridge over the river, noted for its arches and traditional construction methods.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a reference point for the arch's mortar techniques.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Historical structure in the city"}]},{"name":"Sess Embankment","aliases":["River Embankment"],"description":"A public area along the river where crowds gather for events.","recentEvents":"Where the parade crowd watches the keystone ceremony and the king's procession.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Key public space in the city"}],"parentLocation":"Erhenrang"},{"name":"Karhide","aliases":["Nation of Karhide"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Orgoreyn Political Tensions","description":"A politically complex nation on Winter, ruled by King Argaven XV.","recentEvents":"Central to the narrative, with Genly Ai navigating its social and political structures.","relationships":[{"location":"Winter","relationship":"Nation on the planet"}]},{"name":"North Fall","aliases":["High North Fall"],"description":"A remote, snowbound region bordering Karhide and Orgoreyn, marked by harsh climate and political tension.","recentEvents":"Estraven discusses aiding Karhidish farmers displaced from the Sinoth Valley, risking political fallout with the king.","relationships":[{"location":"Sassinoth Valley","relationship":"Adjacent border region contested by Karhide and Orgoreyn"},{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of Karhide's northern territory"}]},{"name":"Sassinoth Valley","aliases":["Sinoth Valley"],"arc":"Estraven's Political Maneuvering and Border Dispute (Historical Context)","description":"A valley trapped in political conflict between Karhide and Orgoreyn, where the narrative's central tensions unfold.","recentEvents":"Karhidish farmers launched a foray here, burning an Orgota village and dumping bodies into the Ey River.","relationships":[{"location":"North Fall","relationship":"Part of the contested border region"},{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Historically inhabited by Orgoreyn settlers"},{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Site of political resistance to the Envoy's mission"}]},{"name":"Remny Tower","description":"A tower in Erhenrang where gongs mark the time, symbolizing the city's rigid temporal structure.","recentEvents":"Estraven and Genly Ai hear the gongs signaling midnight as their conversation concludes.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Part of the city's infrastructure"}]},{"name":"Pering Storm-border","aliases":["Storm-border"],"description":"A region in northern Karhide bordering the Pering Ice, known for its harsh climate and the tragic tale of Getheren and Hode.","recentEvents":"The brothers Getheren and Hode vowed kemmering, but their vow was broken after Getheren's brother committed suicide, leading Getheren to flee northward.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Adjacent region"},{"location":"Shath Domain","relationship":"Historical location tied to the brothers' story"}]},{"name":"Pering Ice","aliases":["Pering Glacier"],"description":"A vast glacial sheet covering northern Karhide, contiguous with the Gobrin Ice of Orgoreyn during winter.","recentEvents":"Getheren traveled northward across the Ice, encountering a supernatural realm where the dead dwell.","relationships":[{"location":"Gobrin Ice","relationship":"Contiguous during winter"},{"location":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","relationship":"Site of Getheren's encounter with Hode"}]},{"name":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","aliases":["Blizzard Place"],"description":"A supernatural realm existing within the Pering Ice, where the dead who died in kemmering dwell eternally.","recentEvents":"Getheren met his deceased brother Hode here, who could not speak his name due to his death.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Located within the glacier"},{"location":"Shath Domain","relationship":"Linked to the brothers' tragic history"}]},{"name":"Gobrin Ice","description":"A glacial expanse in Orgoreyn, contiguous with the Pering Ice during winter storms.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a geographical counterpart to the Pering Ice, part of the frozen north.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Contiguous during winter"}]},{"name":"Shath Domain","aliases":["Hearth of Shath"],"description":"A Karhidish domain where the tragic tale of Getheren and Hode originated.","recentEvents":"The brothers' broken vow and Getheren's exile began here, leading to his journey north.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Storm-border","relationship":"Historical location tied to the brothers' story"}]},{"name":"Orgoreyn","aliases":["Karhide's neighbor"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Orgoreyn Political Tensions","description":"A rival state to Karhide, known for its harsh environment and political tensions.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai contemplates traveling here but hesitates due to potential difficulties returning to Karhide.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Adjacent rival state"}]},{"name":"Fastnesses","arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"A remote eastern region of Karhide containing the Foretellers, who hold significant cultural and prophetic influence.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai resolves to travel here to gather information about Karhide's political dynamics.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Eastern region"}]},{"name":"Grende","aliases":["Grende Region"],"description":"A region in northern Osnoriner, home to Charuthe.","recentEvents":"Herbor travels through the snows of Grende on his way to Charuthe to seek a foretelling for Berosty rem ir Ipe.","relationships":[{"location":"Charuthe","relationship":"Adjacent region"}]},{"name":"New Port","aliases":["New Port"],"description":"A coastal city serving as a departure point for caravans heading east.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai departs from here aboard a trade-caravan bound for the Pering Storm-border.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Storm-border","relationship":"Part of the caravan's route"}]},{"name":"Eskar Pass","aliases":["Eskar Pass"],"description":"A mountain pass through the Kargav range, critical for caravan travel.","recentEvents":"The caravan traverses this pass, encountering extreme weather and avalanches.","relationships":[{"location":"Kargav","relationship":"A key route through the mountain range"}]},{"name":"Ariskostor Fastness","aliases":["Ariskostor Fastness"],"description":"A remote castle-like structure perched on the Kargav's southern face.","recentEvents":"The driver describes it as a residence for the Old Men, inaccessible for most of the year.","relationships":[{"location":"Kargav","relationship":"Located on the mountain range"}]},{"name":"Otherhord","aliases":["Otherhord"],"arc":"Gethenian Cultural Exploration","description":"A secluded Fastness in a forested region, home to the Handdara cult.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai stays here to study the Foretellers' practices and their philosophy of nusuth.","relationships":[{"location":"Fastnesses","relationship":"A specific example of a Handdara retreat"}]},{"name":"Spreve","description":"Domain of the physician from Spreve, a region known for its medical expertise and connection to the Foretellers.","recentEvents":"The physician from Spreve entered the Foretelling circle during the session, interrupting the ritual with a demand for light.","relationships":[{"location":"Otherhord","relationship":"The physician's origin domain"}]},{"name":"Kuseben","aliases":["Kuseben"],"description":"A coastal town in Karhide where Estraven meets Ashe and attempts to flee exile.","recentEvents":"Estraven arrives in Kuseben after fleeing Erhenrang, meets Ashe, and tries to escape to Orgoreyn by sea.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Bordering region; Estraven's escape route"}]},{"name":"Shelt Port","aliases":["Shelt"],"description":"A port city in Orgoreyn where Estraven is set ashore after being intercepted by patrol.","recentEvents":"Estraven is rescued by the Kuseben Patrol and landed here, leading to his detention in the Commensal Hospital.","relationships":[{"location":"Charisune Coastal Area Four","relationship":"Adjacent coastal region"}]},{"name":"Markets of South Mishnory","aliases":["South Mishnory Markets"],"description":"A bustling market hub in Mishnory where Estraven finds work as a landboat loader.","recentEvents":"Estraven works in the ice-houses and lodges on Fish Island, navigating Orgoreyn's social and political systems.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Central commercial district"}]},{"name":"Fish Island","aliases":["Fish Island"],"description":"A crowded island near Mishnory's Markets where Estraven lodges with fellow workers.","recentEvents":"Estraven resides here while working in the ice-houses, enduring harsh conditions and social scrutiny.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Residential district"}]},{"name":"Kunderer Embankment","aliases":["Kunderer Embankment"],"description":"A tree-lined area in Mishnory offering respite from the city's heat.","recentEvents":"Estraven retreats here to escape the oppressive summer heat of Mishnory.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Recreational area"}]},{"name":"Charisune Coastal Area Four","aliases":["Charisune Coastal Area Four"],"description":"A coastal region in Orgoreyn housing the Commensal Hospital where Estraven is detained.","recentEvents":"Estraven is hospitalized here after a failed escape attempt, where he encounters the Inspector and physician.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Administrative district"}]},{"name":"Sennethny","aliases":["Sennethny"],"description":"A location within the Twenty-fourth Commensality of Orgoreyn, tied to Estraven's hospital stay.","recentEvents":"Estraven is registered as a dependent in this commensality after his hospitalization.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Subdivision of the Great Commensality"}]},{"name":"Osnoriner","aliases":["Osnoriner Region"],"description":"A region in Karhide known for its unique divorce practices and social customs.","recentEvents":"Discussed as a place where divorce exists but remarriage after divorce or death is prohibited.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of the Karhide region"}]},{"name":"Perunter","aliases":["Perunter Continent"],"description":"An Antarctic continent where incest between generations is reportedly permitted, though disputed.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a possible location with different social norms regarding incest.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Adjacent or nearby region"}]},{"name":"Gorinhering","aliases":["Gorinhering Clan-Hearth"],"description":"A Clan-Hearth on Karhide's Eastern coast, built on a hill above the Hodomin Ocean.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai resided here during the summer, interacting with locals and observing Karhidish culture.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of the Eastern coastal region"},{"location":"Hodomin Ocean","relationship":"Surrounded by the eternal fogs of this ocean"}]},{"name":"Ey River","description":"A glacier-fed border river between Karhide and Orgoreyn, marked by a bridge connecting Passerer and Siuwensin.","recentEvents":"A Karhidish foray raided Siuwensin, prompting Genly's journey into Orgoreyn.","relationships":[{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Karhidish village across the river"},{"location":"Siuwensin","relationship":"Orgota village across the river"}]},{"name":"Passerer","description":"A Karhidish village on the Karhide side of the Ey River bridge.","recentEvents":"A foray from Passerer raids Siuwensin, causing widespread destruction.","relationships":[{"location":"Ey River","relationship":"Located across the river from Siuwensin"},{"location":"Ovord Domain","relationship":"Alleged origin of foray guns"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent Commensal territory"}]},{"name":"Siuwensin","arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Orgoreyn Political Tensions","description":"An Orgota village on the Orgoreyn side of the Ey River bridge.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai and refugees are detained here after a raid, interrogated, and held in a storage-barn overnight.","relationships":[{"location":"Ey River","relationship":"Located across the river from Passerer"},{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Source of the raiding foray"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent inspection point"}]},{"name":"Commensal Border-Station","description":"An Orgote border checkpoint where Genly obtained a permiso for travel.","recentEvents":"Processed Genly's entry into Orgoreyn after verifying his credentials.","relationships":[{"location":"Siuwensin","relationship":"Adjacent to the Commensal Transient-House"}]},{"name":"Ovord Domain","aliases":["Ovord Domain"],"description":"A Commensal region accused of supplying foray guns to Passerer.","recentEvents":"Whispers suggest Ovord Domain's involvement in the Siuwensin raid via foray guns.","relationships":[{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Alleged supplier of foray weapons"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent Commensal territory"}]},{"name":"Icefoot Lake","aliases":["Icefoot"],"description":"A frozen lake in Kerm Land where key events unfold.","recentEvents":"Young Estraven falls through the ice, is rescued by Therem of Stok, and later wounded during a hunt.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of Kerm Land"}]},{"name":"Ebos village","description":"A village on the north shore of Icefoot Lake.","recentEvents":"Estraven is taken here after being injured, then later the village sends people to retrieve Estraven's body.","relationships":[{"location":"Icefoot Lake","relationship":"Adjacent"}]},{"name":"Rotherer Fastness","description":"A remote fastness where Therem of Stok resides for a year.","recentEvents":"Therem indwells here after being exiled, later returning to Estre as its new lord.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of Kerm Land"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Genly Ai's Mission and Orgoreyn Political Tensions","status":"active","characters":["Genly Ai","King Argaven XV","Pemmer Harge rem ir Tibe"],"summary":"Ai arrives in Mishnory after navigating Orgote bureaucracy, now confronting political tensions between Karhide and Orgoreyn. His mission continues as he interacts with Orgote officials and learns of the raid on Siuwensin."},{"name":"Estraven's Exile and Cross-National Political Struggles","status":"active","characters":["Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","Foreth rem ir Osboth"],"summary":"Estraven's presence in Mishnory and the delivery of Foreth's money highlight his ongoing struggle for survival and political influence. His connection to the raid on Siuwensin underscores his role in the Karhide-Orgoreyn conflict."},{"name":"Gethenian Cultural Exploration","status":"active","characters":["Genly Ai","Commensal Slose","Commensal Obsle"],"summary":"Ai's observations of Orgote culture deepen as he interacts with Commensals, contrasting their structured society with Karhide's clan-based systems. The cultural exchange continues through conversations about Gethen's environment and philosophy."}],"summary":"The chapter recounts a tale of estranged rivals Estraven and Arek, whose feud culminates in Estraven's death and the birth of a child raised as Therem. After years of conflict, Therem becomes Lord of Estre, ending the feud by ceding disputed lands to Stok. The narrative highlights themes of betrayal, reconciliation, and the cyclical nature of conflict."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":13,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Genly Ai","aliases":["Mr. Ai","the Envoy"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"The Ekumen's Envoy to Karhide, struggling with the political and psychological complexities of his mission.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Former contact; Estraven is now the King’s Ear"},{"character":"King Argaven XV","relationship":"The monarch he is attempting to persuade to join the Ekumen"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed bureaucratic structures with Shusgis, debated Estraven's loyalty"},{"name":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","aliases":["The King’s Ear","Lord Estraven"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A nobleman from the Domain of Estre, known for his complex relationship with Genly Ai and his role in ending the feud between Estre and Stok.","relationships":[{"character":"King Argaven XV","relationship":"Formerly the king's closest confidant and advisor"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Allied through covert communication and financial support"},{"character":"Foreth rem ir Osboth","relationship":"Former kemmering (male companion)"}],"recentEvents":"Confrontation with Genly Ai, warning about factional manipulation"},{"name":"King Argaven XV","aliases":["the king"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Royal House","description":"The paranoid and volatile ruler of Karhide, suspicious of foreign influence and internal dissent.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Formerly his most trusted advisor, now exiled"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"The Envoy whose mission he resists and interrogates"}],"recentEvents":"Child's birth and death, political speculation about succession"},{"name":"Pemmer Harge rem ir Tibe","aliases":["the king’s cousin"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The king’s cousin and a member of the upper chamber, known for his rivalry with Estraven.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Rival and political adversary"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Interacted during the dinner conversation"}],"recentEvents":"Featured in news about Karhide’s territorial claims in the Sinoth Valley"},{"name":"servant","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"1. A Parade in Erhenrang","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Karhidish servant who left after the meal.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Departed to their home after the meal, as Karhiders do not employ bonded labor."},{"name":"Getheren","aliases":["Ennoch"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Brother who survived the exile and journey to the Ice, met his brother Hode in the Place Inside the Blizzard.","relationships":[{"character":"Hode","relationship":"Brother"}],"recentEvents":"Traveled to the Pering Ice, encountered Hode, died after returning to Shath and revealing his identity."},{"name":"Hode","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","description":"Getheren's brother who committed suicide after being exiled, now resides in the Place Inside the Blizzard.","relationships":[{"character":"Getheren","relationship":"Brother"}],"recentEvents":"Died by suicide, appeared to Getheren in the Place Inside the Blizzard as a white, lifeless figure."},{"name":"the traveler","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Carried Getheren's message back to Shath, confirming the domain's recovery after Getheren's death.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received Getheren's final message and relayed it to Shath, contributing to the domain's restoration."},{"name":"Lord Berosty rem ir Ipe","aliases":["Ashe Berosty rem ir Ipe"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"4. The Nineteenth Day","currentLocation":"Grende","description":"A nobleman who sought a Foretelling about his death and later killed his kemmering Herbor before dying by suicide.","relationships":[{"character":"Herbor of the Geganner clan","relationship":"kemmering"}],"recentEvents":"Received a Foretelling about his death, killed Herbor, and hanged himself on Odstreth."},{"name":"Herbor of the Geganner clan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"4. The Nineteenth Day","currentLocation":"Grende","description":"A poor man who sought a Foretelling to save his kemmering Berosty rem ir Ipe.","relationships":[{"character":"Lord Berosty rem ir Ipe","relationship":"kemmering"}],"recentEvents":"Sought a Foretelling, was killed by Berosty, and died from the injury."},{"name":"Weaver Odren","aliases":["The Weaver","the Weaver","Faxe"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Otherhord","description":"A Foreteller and the Weaver of the group, known for his role in the Foretelling sessions.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Envoy and seeker of answers"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted the Foretelling session for Genly Ai, where he answered the question about Gethen's membership in the Ekumen."},{"name":"Goss","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Otherhord","description":"A young Indweller who guides Genly Ai to the Fastness of Otherhord.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Guide and companion"}],"recentEvents":"Led Genly Ai to Otherhord and engaged in conversation about the Handdara"},{"name":"the driver","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"on the caravan","description":"The driver of the landboats guiding the caravan through the Kargav.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Guided the caravan and shared stories about the Fastnesses"},{"name":"the physician from Spreve","aliases":["the physician"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Otherhord","description":"A physician from Spreve who entered the circle during the Foretelling session.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Entered the circle during the Foretelling session, contributing to the disruption of the session."},{"name":"the cook","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"6. One Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A servant who wakes Therem Harth","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Helped Therem escape by providing food"},{"name":"the fisherman","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"6. One Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A fisherman who initially refused to help Therem","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Refused to assist Therem but later led to his capture"},{"name":"The Inspector","aliases":["Inspector"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Commensal Border-Station","description":"A government official handling refugee interrogations and border controls.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of bureaucratic oversight"},{"name":"Commensal Yegey","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Host at the lunch gathering, curious about the Ekumen.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Maintains dependent relationship"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Host"}],"recentEvents":"Mentioned as Estraven's patron"},{"name":"Commensal Obsle","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Commensal with political tensions regarding Estraven","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Politically entangled"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Interrogator"}],"recentEvents":"Expressed distrust of Estraven's loyalty"},{"name":"Foreth rem ir Osboth","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"8. Another Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Orgny Fastness","description":"Estraven's former kemmering, now an Indweller at Orgny Fastness.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Debt owed for aiding Estraven"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Genly Ai money to deliver to Estraven, expressing hope for his survival."},{"name":"the baby","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"8. Another Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"","relationships":[]},{"name":"Arek of Estre","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The heir of the Domain of Estre, who was killed by a Stok warrior during a feud between the two domains.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Killed by a Stok warrior while traveling through the thore-forest, his body left to be eaten by wild beasts."},{"name":"The murderer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Stok warrior who killed Arek of Estre during the feud between the domains.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Stabbed Arek of Estre to death and left his body to be eaten by wild beasts."},{"name":"The men from Stok","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A group of Stok warriors who disobeyed their lord's orders and left Arek of Estre's body to be eaten by wild beasts.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Disobeyed their lord's command to bury Arek of Estre, leading to their banishment."},{"name":"Lord Sorve","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The lord of the Domain of Estre who died, leaving his heir Therem to inherit the domain.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Died, leading to Therem becoming Lord of Estre and ending the feud with Stok."},{"name":"The old lord","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Estre","description":"The lord of the Domain of Estre who adopted the child of Arek of Estre as his heir.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Adopted the child of Arek of Estre and named him Therem, who later became Lord of Estre."},{"name":"The people from Ebos village","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Residents of Ebos village who helped Therem of Stok after he was wounded.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Carried Therem of Stok back to Estre after he was wounded in the thore-forest."},{"name":"Mersen","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Karhidish agent suspected of espionage.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Suspected informant"},{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Suspected of espionage"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed as a spy for Tibe, target of political suspicion"},{"name":"Gaum","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Agent of secret police, manipulative figure","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Curious observer"},{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Politically adversarial"}],"recentEvents":"Confirmed as secret police agent, scheming against Ai"},{"name":"Humery","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Fat old man in purple, skeptical of interstellar trade.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Expressed disgust at interstellar travel"},{"name":"Slose","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Commensal eager for political change.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Advocate for Ekumen"}],"recentEvents":"Pushed for interstellar trade, religious fervor"},{"name":"The fat old man in purple","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Skeptical diner at the lunch gathering.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Expressed disgust at interstellar travel"},{"name":"Shusgis","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Commensal with knowledge of Orgoreyn's bureaucracy","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Provided information about Sarf and political factions"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed Orgoreyn's secret police, Estraven's status, and political factions"}],"locations":[{"name":"Erhenrang","aliases":["Capital City","City of Karhide","Arch of the River Gate","New Road and River Port","Island","Genly's Lodgings","Winter","Planet Winter","Gethen"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"The capital city of Karhide, known for its grand architecture and political significance. A monumental structure completed to enhance Erhenrang's trade and infrastructure. A communal living space for foreigners in Erhenrang, where Genly Ai resides. The icy planet where Karhide is located, with extreme seasonal variations.","recentEvents":"Hosted a parade celebrating the completion of the Arch of the River Gate, where Genly Ai interacts with key figures like King Argaven XV and Therem Harth rem ir Estraven.; Central to the parade, with the king and masons participating in its final assembly.; Where Genly Ai reflects on his isolation and observes local customs.; Setting for the entire narrative, with Genly Ai navigating its harsh climate and politics.","relationships":[{"location":"Royal House","relationship":"Contains the royal residence and administrative center"},{"location":"Palace of Erhenrang","relationship":"Part of the city's walled inner complex"}]},{"name":"Royal House","aliases":["King's Residence","Royal Palace"],"arc":"Estraven's Exile and Cross-National Political Struggles","description":"The fortified palace complex housing the king and key political figures.","recentEvents":"Served as the backdrop for the royal procession and the keystone-laying ceremony.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Central structure within the city"},{"location":"King's House","relationship":"Part of the same complex"}]},{"name":"Corner Red Dwelling","aliases":["Estraven's Home"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"A historic residence of Therem Harth rem ir Estraven, symbolizing his political influence.","recentEvents":"Where Genly Ai is invited for dinner, revealing shifting power dynamics.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Located within the city's walls"}]},{"name":"Old Bridge","aliases":["Ancient Bridge"],"description":"A historic bridge over the river, noted for its arches and traditional construction methods.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a reference point for the arch's mortar techniques.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Historical structure in the city"}]},{"name":"Sess Embankment","aliases":["River Embankment"],"description":"A public area along the river where crowds gather for events.","recentEvents":"Where the parade crowd watches the keystone ceremony and the king's procession.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Key public space in the city"}],"parentLocation":"Erhenrang"},{"name":"Karhide","aliases":["Nation of Karhide"],"arc":"Estraven's Exile and Cross-National Political Struggles","description":"A politically complex nation on Winter, ruled by King Argaven XV.","recentEvents":"Central to the narrative, with Genly Ai navigating its social and political structures.","relationships":[{"location":"Winter","relationship":"Nation on the planet"}]},{"name":"North Fall","aliases":["High North Fall"],"description":"A remote, snowbound region bordering Karhide and Orgoreyn, marked by harsh climate and political tension.","recentEvents":"Estraven discusses aiding Karhidish farmers displaced from the Sinoth Valley, risking political fallout with the king.","relationships":[{"location":"Sassinoth Valley","relationship":"Adjacent border region contested by Karhide and Orgoreyn"},{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of Karhide's northern territory"}]},{"name":"Sassinoth Valley","aliases":["Sinoth Valley"],"arc":"Estraven's Political Maneuvering and Border Dispute (Historical Context)","description":"A valley trapped in political conflict between Karhide and Orgoreyn, where the narrative's central tensions unfold.","recentEvents":"Karhidish farmers launched a foray here, burning an Orgota village and dumping bodies into the Ey River.","relationships":[{"location":"North Fall","relationship":"Part of the contested border region"},{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Historically inhabited by Orgoreyn settlers"},{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Site of political resistance to the Envoy's mission"}]},{"name":"Remny Tower","description":"A tower in Erhenrang where gongs mark the time, symbolizing the city's rigid temporal structure.","recentEvents":"Estraven and Genly Ai hear the gongs signaling midnight as their conversation concludes.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Part of the city's infrastructure"}]},{"name":"Pering Storm-border","aliases":["Storm-border"],"description":"A region in northern Karhide bordering the Pering Ice, known for its harsh climate and the tragic tale of Getheren and Hode.","recentEvents":"The brothers Getheren and Hode vowed kemmering, but their vow was broken after Getheren's brother committed suicide, leading Getheren to flee northward.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Adjacent region"},{"location":"Shath Domain","relationship":"Historical location tied to the brothers' story"}]},{"name":"Pering Ice","aliases":["Pering Glacier"],"description":"A vast glacial sheet covering northern Karhide, contiguous with the Gobrin Ice of Orgoreyn during winter.","recentEvents":"Getheren traveled northward across the Ice, encountering a supernatural realm where the dead dwell.","relationships":[{"location":"Gobrin Ice","relationship":"Contiguous during winter"},{"location":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","relationship":"Site of Getheren's encounter with Hode"}]},{"name":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","aliases":["Blizzard Place"],"description":"A supernatural realm existing within the Pering Ice, where the dead who died in kemmering dwell eternally.","recentEvents":"Getheren met his deceased brother Hode here, who could not speak his name due to his death.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Located within the glacier"},{"location":"Shath Domain","relationship":"Linked to the brothers' tragic history"}]},{"name":"Gobrin Ice","description":"A glacial expanse in Orgoreyn, contiguous with the Pering Ice during winter storms.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a geographical counterpart to the Pering Ice, part of the frozen north.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Contiguous during winter"}]},{"name":"Shath Domain","aliases":["Hearth of Shath"],"description":"A Karhidish domain where the tragic tale of Getheren and Hode originated.","recentEvents":"The brothers' broken vow and Getheren's exile began here, leading to his journey north.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Storm-border","relationship":"Historical location tied to the brothers' story"}]},{"name":"Orgoreyn","aliases":["Karhide's neighbor"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Orgoreyn Political Tensions","description":"A rival state to Karhide, known for its harsh environment and political tensions.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai contemplates traveling here but hesitates due to potential difficulties returning to Karhide.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Adjacent rival state"}]},{"name":"Fastnesses","arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"A remote eastern region of Karhide containing the Foretellers, who hold significant cultural and prophetic influence.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai resolves to travel here to gather information about Karhide's political dynamics.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Eastern region"}]},{"name":"Grende","aliases":["Grende Region"],"description":"A region in northern Osnoriner, home to Charuthe.","recentEvents":"Herbor travels through the snows of Grende on his way to Charuthe to seek a foretelling for Berosty rem ir Ipe.","relationships":[{"location":"Charuthe","relationship":"Adjacent region"}]},{"name":"New Port","aliases":["New Port"],"description":"A coastal city serving as a departure point for caravans heading east.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai departs from here aboard a trade-caravan bound for the Pering Storm-border.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Storm-border","relationship":"Part of the caravan's route"}]},{"name":"Eskar Pass","aliases":["Eskar Pass"],"description":"A mountain pass through the Kargav range, critical for caravan travel.","recentEvents":"The caravan traverses this pass, encountering extreme weather and avalanches.","relationships":[{"location":"Kargav","relationship":"A key route through the mountain range"}]},{"name":"Ariskostor Fastness","aliases":["Ariskostor Fastness"],"description":"A remote castle-like structure perched on the Kargav's southern face.","recentEvents":"The driver describes it as a residence for the Old Men, inaccessible for most of the year.","relationships":[{"location":"Kargav","relationship":"Located on the mountain range"}]},{"name":"Otherhord","aliases":["Otherhord"],"arc":"Gethenian Cultural Exploration","description":"A secluded Fastness in a forested region, home to the Handdara cult.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai stays here to study the Foretellers' practices and their philosophy of nusuth.","relationships":[{"location":"Fastnesses","relationship":"A specific example of a Handdara retreat"}]},{"name":"Spreve","description":"Domain of the physician from Spreve, a region known for its medical expertise and connection to the Foretellers.","recentEvents":"The physician from Spreve entered the Foretelling circle during the session, interrupting the ritual with a demand for light.","relationships":[{"location":"Otherhord","relationship":"The physician's origin domain"}]},{"name":"Kuseben","aliases":["Kuseben"],"description":"A coastal town in Karhide where Estraven meets Ashe and attempts to flee exile.","recentEvents":"Estraven arrives in Kuseben after fleeing Erhenrang, meets Ashe, and tries to escape to Orgoreyn by sea.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Bordering region; Estraven's escape route"}]},{"name":"Shelt Port","aliases":["Shelt"],"description":"A port city in Orgoreyn where Estraven is set ashore after being intercepted by patrol.","recentEvents":"Estraven is rescued by the Kuseben Patrol and landed here, leading to his detention in the Commensal Hospital.","relationships":[{"location":"Charisune Coastal Area Four","relationship":"Adjacent coastal region"}]},{"name":"Markets of South Mishnory","aliases":["South Mishnory Markets"],"description":"A bustling market hub in Mishnory where Estraven finds work as a landboat loader.","recentEvents":"Estraven works in the ice-houses and lodges on Fish Island, navigating Orgoreyn's social and political systems.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Central commercial district"}]},{"name":"Fish Island","aliases":["Fish Island"],"description":"A crowded island near Mishnory's Markets where Estraven lodges with fellow workers.","recentEvents":"Estraven resides here while working in the ice-houses, enduring harsh conditions and social scrutiny.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Residential district"}]},{"name":"Kunderer Embankment","aliases":["Kunderer Embankment"],"description":"A tree-lined area in Mishnory offering respite from the city's heat.","recentEvents":"Estraven retreats here to escape the oppressive summer heat of Mishnory.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Recreational area"}]},{"name":"Charisune Coastal Area Four","aliases":["Charisune Coastal Area Four"],"description":"A coastal region in Orgoreyn housing the Commensal Hospital where Estraven is detained.","recentEvents":"Estraven is hospitalized here after a failed escape attempt, where he encounters the Inspector and physician.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Administrative district"}]},{"name":"Sennethny","aliases":["Sennethny"],"description":"A location within the Twenty-fourth Commensality of Orgoreyn, tied to Estraven's hospital stay.","recentEvents":"Estraven is registered as a dependent in this commensality after his hospitalization.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Subdivision of the Great Commensality"}]},{"name":"Osnoriner","aliases":["Osnoriner Region"],"description":"A region in Karhide known for its unique divorce practices and social customs.","recentEvents":"Discussed as a place where divorce exists but remarriage after divorce or death is prohibited.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of the Karhide region"}]},{"name":"Perunter","aliases":["Perunter Continent"],"description":"An Antarctic continent where incest between generations is reportedly permitted, though disputed.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a possible location with different social norms regarding incest.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Adjacent or nearby region"}]},{"name":"Gorinhering","aliases":["Gorinhering Clan-Hearth"],"description":"A Clan-Hearth on Karhide's Eastern coast, built on a hill above the Hodomin Ocean.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai resided here during the summer, interacting with locals and observing Karhidish culture.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of the Eastern coastal region"},{"location":"Hodomin Ocean","relationship":"Surrounded by the eternal fogs of this ocean"}]},{"name":"Ey River","description":"A glacier-fed border river between Karhide and Orgoreyn, marked by a bridge connecting Passerer and Siuwensin.","recentEvents":"A Karhidish foray raided Siuwensin, prompting Genly's journey into Orgoreyn.","relationships":[{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Karhidish village across the river"},{"location":"Siuwensin","relationship":"Orgota village across the river"}]},{"name":"Passerer","description":"A Karhidish village on the Karhide side of the Ey River bridge.","recentEvents":"A foray from Passerer raids Siuwensin, causing widespread destruction.","relationships":[{"location":"Ey River","relationship":"Located across the river from Siuwensin"},{"location":"Ovord Domain","relationship":"Alleged origin of foray guns"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent Commensal territory"}]},{"name":"Siuwensin","arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Orgoreyn Political Tensions","description":"An Orgota village on the Orgoreyn side of the Ey River bridge.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai and refugees are detained here after a raid, interrogated, and held in a storage-barn overnight.","relationships":[{"location":"Ey River","relationship":"Located across the river from Passerer"},{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Source of the raiding foray"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent inspection point"}]},{"name":"Commensal Border-Station","description":"An Orgote border checkpoint where Genly obtained a permiso for travel.","recentEvents":"Processed Genly's entry into Orgoreyn after verifying his credentials.","relationships":[{"location":"Siuwensin","relationship":"Adjacent to the Commensal Transient-House"}]},{"name":"Ovord Domain","aliases":["Ovord Domain"],"description":"A Commensal region accused of supplying foray guns to Passerer.","recentEvents":"Whispers suggest Ovord Domain's involvement in the Siuwensin raid via foray guns.","relationships":[{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Alleged supplier of foray weapons"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent Commensal territory"}]},{"name":"Icefoot Lake","aliases":["Icefoot"],"description":"A frozen lake in Kerm Land where key events unfold.","recentEvents":"Young Estraven falls through the ice, is rescued by Therem of Stok, and later wounded during a hunt.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of Kerm Land"}]},{"name":"Ebos village","description":"A village on the north shore of Icefoot Lake.","recentEvents":"Estraven is taken here after being injured, then later the village sends people to retrieve Estraven's body.","relationships":[{"location":"Icefoot Lake","relationship":"Adjacent"}]},{"name":"Rotherer Fastness","description":"A remote fastness where Therem of Stok resides for a year.","recentEvents":"Therem indwells here after being exiled, later returning to Estre as its new lord.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of Kerm Land"}]},{"name":"Artisan School","aliases":["Royal Workshop Foundry"],"description":"A central institution in Karhide where technological and artistic craftsmanship is practiced.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai mentions the ship's components are stored here after landing on Horden Island.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Horden Island","description":"A remote island where Genly Ai first landed on Gethen, serving as a temporary base for his mission.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai's arrival and subsequent departure from the island were discussed during conversations in Mishnory.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Linked via transportation"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Genly Ai's Mission and Orgoreyn Political Tensions","status":"active","characters":["Genly Ai","Shusgis","Gaum","Obsle","Commensals"],"summary":"Genly uncovers Orgoreyn's bureaucratic complexity, learning that Gaum is a Sarf agent and Estraven is a dependent of Yegey. Political factions manipulate him, with Shusgis revealing Estraven's suspected treachery and the Sarf's role in controlling dissent."},{"name":"Estraven's Exile and Cross-National Political Struggles","status":"active","characters":["Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","Yegey","Obsle","Mersen","Tibe"],"summary":"Estraven's ambiguous loyalties and exile deepen as factions vie for influence. Shusgis labels him a traitor, highlighting his precarious position between Karhide, Orgoreyn, and the Open Trade movement."},{"name":"Gethenian Cultural Exploration","status":"active","characters":["Genly Ai","Commensals","Shusgis"],"summary":"Genly's attempts to engage with Gethenian culture are overshadowed by political intrigue, though his discussions with Commensals about the Ekumen's philosophy persist amid skepticism and factional agendas."}],"summary":"Genly Ai navigates political intrigue in Mishnory, grappling with Estraven's ambiguous loyalties and the complex bureaucracy of Orgoreyn. The chapter reveals tensions between factions, with Shusgis hinting at Estraven's treasonous past and the shadowy influence of the Sarf bureau. Ai feels a pervasive sense of insubstantiality among the people, questioning their authenticity and the solidity of his own perceptions."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":14,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Genly Ai","aliases":["Mr. Ai","the Envoy"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"The Ekumen's Envoy to Karhide, struggling with the political and psychological complexities of his mission.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Former contact; Estraven is now the King’s Ear"},{"character":"King Argaven XV","relationship":"The monarch he is attempting to persuade to join the Ekumen"}],"recentEvents":"Spoke in the Hall of the Thirty-Three, faced interruptions and skepticism from Domination faction members."},{"name":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","aliases":["The King’s Ear","Lord Estraven"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A nobleman from the Domain of Estre, known for his complex relationship with Genly Ai and his role in ending the feud between Estre and Stok.","relationships":[{"character":"King Argaven XV","relationship":"Formerly the king's closest confidant and advisor"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Allied through covert communication and financial support"},{"character":"Foreth rem ir Osboth","relationship":"Former kemmering (male companion)"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed the Envoy's safety with Estraven, hesitated to publicize his mission due to Sarf control."},{"name":"King Argaven XV","aliases":["the king"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Royal House","description":"The paranoid and volatile ruler of Karhide, suspicious of foreign influence and internal dissent.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Formerly his most trusted advisor, now exiled"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"The Envoy whose mission he resists and interrogates"}],"recentEvents":"Child's birth and death, political speculation about succession"},{"name":"Pemmer Harge rem ir Tibe","aliases":["the king’s cousin"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The king’s cousin and a member of the upper chamber, known for his rivalry with Estraven.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Rival and political adversary"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Interacted during the dinner conversation"}],"recentEvents":"Featured in news about Karhide’s territorial claims in the Sinoth Valley"},{"name":"servant","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"1. A Parade in Erhenrang","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Karhidish servant who left after the meal.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Departed to their home after the meal, as Karhiders do not employ bonded labor."},{"name":"Getheren","aliases":["Ennoch"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Brother who survived the exile and journey to the Ice, met his brother Hode in the Place Inside the Blizzard.","relationships":[{"character":"Hode","relationship":"Brother"}],"recentEvents":"Traveled to the Pering Ice, encountered Hode, died after returning to Shath and revealing his identity."},{"name":"Hode","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","description":"Getheren's brother who committed suicide after being exiled, now resides in the Place Inside the Blizzard.","relationships":[{"character":"Getheren","relationship":"Brother"}],"recentEvents":"Died by suicide, appeared to Getheren in the Place Inside the Blizzard as a white, lifeless figure."},{"name":"the traveler","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Carried Getheren's message back to Shath, confirming the domain's recovery after Getheren's death.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received Getheren's final message and relayed it to Shath, contributing to the domain's restoration."},{"name":"Lord Berosty rem ir Ipe","aliases":["Ashe Berosty rem ir Ipe"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"4. The Nineteenth Day","currentLocation":"Grende","description":"A nobleman who sought a Foretelling about his death and later killed his kemmering Herbor before dying by suicide.","relationships":[{"character":"Herbor of the Geganner clan","relationship":"kemmering"}],"recentEvents":"Received a Foretelling about his death, killed Herbor, and hanged himself on Odstreth."},{"name":"Herbor of the Geganner clan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"4. The Nineteenth Day","currentLocation":"Grende","description":"A poor man who sought a Foretelling to save his kemmering Berosty rem ir Ipe.","relationships":[{"character":"Lord Berosty rem ir Ipe","relationship":"kemmering"}],"recentEvents":"Sought a Foretelling, was killed by Berosty, and died from the injury."},{"name":"Weaver Odren","aliases":["The Weaver","the Weaver","Faxe"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Otherhord","description":"A Foreteller and the Weaver of the group, known for his role in the Foretelling sessions.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Envoy and seeker of answers"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted the Foretelling session for Genly Ai, where he answered the question about Gethen's membership in the Ekumen."},{"name":"Goss","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Otherhord","description":"A young Indweller who guides Genly Ai to the Fastness of Otherhord.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Guide and companion"}],"recentEvents":"Led Genly Ai to Otherhord and engaged in conversation about the Handdara"},{"name":"the driver","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"on the caravan","description":"The driver of the landboats guiding the caravan through the Kargav.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Guided the caravan and shared stories about the Fastnesses"},{"name":"the physician from Spreve","aliases":["the physician"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Otherhord","description":"A physician from Spreve who entered the circle during the Foretelling session.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Entered the circle during the Foretelling session, contributing to the disruption of the session."},{"name":"the cook","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"6. One Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A servant who wakes Therem Harth","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Helped Therem escape by providing food"},{"name":"the fisherman","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"6. One Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A fisherman who initially refused to help Therem","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Refused to assist Therem but later led to his capture"},{"name":"The Inspector","aliases":["Inspector"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Commensal Border-Station","description":"A government official handling refugee interrogations and border controls.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of bureaucratic oversight"},{"name":"Commensal Yegey","aliases":["Yegey"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Host at the lunch gathering, curious about the Ekumen.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Maintains dependent relationship"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Host"}],"recentEvents":"Opposed the blockade of grain-exports to Karhide during the Hall session."},{"name":"Commensal Obsle","aliases":["Obsle"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Commensal with political tensions regarding Estraven","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Politically entangled"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Interrogator"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed the Envoy's radio contact with the Star Ship, hesitated due to Sarf control."},{"name":"Foreth rem ir Osboth","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"8. Another Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Orgny Fastness","description":"Estraven's former kemmering, now an Indweller at Orgny Fastness.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Debt owed for aiding Estraven"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Genly Ai money to deliver to Estraven, expressing hope for his survival."},{"name":"the baby","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"8. Another Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"","relationships":[]},{"name":"Arek of Estre","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The heir of the Domain of Estre, who was killed by a Stok warrior during a feud between the two domains.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Killed by a Stok warrior while traveling through the thore-forest, his body left to be eaten by wild beasts."},{"name":"The murderer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Stok warrior who killed Arek of Estre during the feud between the domains.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Stabbed Arek of Estre to death and left his body to be eaten by wild beasts."},{"name":"The men from Stok","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A group of Stok warriors who disobeyed their lord's orders and left Arek of Estre's body to be eaten by wild beasts.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Disobeyed their lord's command to bury Arek of Estre, leading to their banishment."},{"name":"Lord Sorve","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The lord of the Domain of Estre who died, leaving his heir Therem to inherit the domain.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Died, leading to Therem becoming Lord of Estre and ending the feud with Stok."},{"name":"The old lord","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Estre","description":"The lord of the Domain of Estre who adopted the child of Arek of Estre as his heir.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Adopted the child of Arek of Estre and named him Therem, who later became Lord of Estre."},{"name":"The people from Ebos village","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Residents of Ebos village who helped Therem of Stok after he was wounded.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Carried Therem of Stok back to Estre after he was wounded in the thore-forest."},{"name":"Mersen","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Karhidish agent suspected of espionage.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Suspected informant"},{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Suspected of espionage"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed as a spy for Tibe, target of political suspicion"},{"name":"Gaum","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A member of the Sarf who attempted to seduce Estraven during kemmer.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Curious observer"},{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Politically adversarial"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to seduce Estraven during kemmer, failed due to Estraven's abstinence."},{"name":"Humery","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Fat old man in purple, skeptical of interstellar trade.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Expressed disgust at interstellar travel"},{"name":"Slose","aliases":["Commensal Slose"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A Commensal and mystic who interpreted the Envoy's mission as a spiritual event.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Advocate for Ekumen"}],"recentEvents":"Led a committee to suppress obscene plays, interpreted the Envoy's mission as a spiritual event."},{"name":"The fat old man in purple","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Skeptical diner at the lunch gathering.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Expressed disgust at interstellar travel"},{"name":"Shusgis","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Commensal with knowledge of Orgoreyn's bureaucracy","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Provided information about Sarf and political factions"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed Orgoreyn's secret police, Estraven's status, and political factions"},{"name":"Csl. Ithepen of the Eynyen District","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A member of the Thirty-Three who proposed inviting the Star Ship to Orgoreyn.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Proposed to Obsle to invite the Star Ship to Orgoreyn, but the plan was rejected."},{"name":"Alshel","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Presiding officer in the Hall of the Thirty-Three during the Envoy's speech.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Presided over the session where the Envoy spoke about the Star Ship."},{"name":"Kaharosile","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A member of the Domination faction who interrupted the Envoy's speech with accusations.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Interrupted the session with accusations against the Envoy, claiming he was a Karhidish agent."}],"locations":[{"name":"Erhenrang","aliases":["Capital City","City of Karhide","Arch of the River Gate","New Road and River Port","Island","Genly's Lodgings","Winter","Planet Winter","Gethen","Old Bridge","Ancient Bridge"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"The capital city of Karhide, known for its grand architecture and political significance. A monumental structure completed to enhance Erhenrang's trade and infrastructure. A communal living space for foreigners in Erhenrang, where Genly Ai resides. The icy planet where Karhide is located, with extreme seasonal variations. A historic bridge over the river, noted for its arches and traditional construction methods.","recentEvents":"Hosted a parade celebrating the completion of the Arch of the River Gate, where Genly Ai interacts with key figures like King Argaven XV and Therem Harth rem ir Estraven.; Central to the parade, with the king and masons participating in its final assembly.; Where Genly Ai reflects on his isolation and observes local customs.; Setting for the entire narrative, with Genly Ai navigating its harsh climate and politics.; Mentioned as a reference point for the arch's mortar techniques.","relationships":[{"location":"Royal House","relationship":"Contains the royal residence and administrative center"},{"location":"Palace of Erhenrang","relationship":"Part of the city's walled inner complex"}]},{"name":"Royal House","aliases":["King's Residence","Royal Palace"],"arc":"Estraven's Exile and Cross-National Political Struggles","description":"The fortified palace complex housing the king and key political figures.","recentEvents":"Served as the backdrop for the royal procession and the keystone-laying ceremony.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Central structure within the city"},{"location":"King's House","relationship":"Part of the same complex"}]},{"name":"Corner Red Dwelling","aliases":["Estraven's Home"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"A historic residence of Therem Harth rem ir Estraven, symbolizing his political influence.","recentEvents":"Where Genly Ai is invited for dinner, revealing shifting power dynamics.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Located within the city's walls"}]},{"name":"Sess Embankment","aliases":["River Embankment"],"description":"A public area along the river where crowds gather for events.","recentEvents":"Where the parade crowd watches the keystone ceremony and the king's procession.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Key public space in the city"}],"parentLocation":"Erhenrang"},{"name":"Karhide","aliases":["Nation of Karhide"],"arc":"Estraven's Exile and Cross-National Political Struggles","description":"A politically complex nation on Winter, ruled by King Argaven XV.","recentEvents":"Central to the narrative, with Genly Ai navigating its social and political structures.","relationships":[{"location":"Winter","relationship":"Nation on the planet"}]},{"name":"North Fall","aliases":["High North Fall"],"description":"A remote, snowbound region bordering Karhide and Orgoreyn, marked by harsh climate and political tension.","recentEvents":"Estraven discusses aiding Karhidish farmers displaced from the Sinoth Valley, risking political fallout with the king.","relationships":[{"location":"Sassinoth Valley","relationship":"Adjacent border region contested by Karhide and Orgoreyn"},{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of Karhide's northern territory"}]},{"name":"Sassinoth Valley","aliases":["Sinoth Valley"],"arc":"Estraven's Political Maneuvering and Border Dispute (Historical Context)","description":"A valley trapped in political conflict between Karhide and Orgoreyn, where the narrative's central tensions unfold.","recentEvents":"Karhidish farmers launched a foray here, burning an Orgota village and dumping bodies into the Ey River.","relationships":[{"location":"North Fall","relationship":"Part of the contested border region"},{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Historically inhabited by Orgoreyn settlers"},{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Site of political resistance to the Envoy's mission"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Remny Tower","description":"A tower in Erhenrang where gongs mark the time, symbolizing the city's rigid temporal structure.","recentEvents":"Estraven and Genly Ai hear the gongs signaling midnight as their conversation concludes.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Part of the city's infrastructure"}]},{"name":"Pering Storm-border","aliases":["Storm-border"],"description":"A region in northern Karhide bordering the Pering Ice, known for its harsh climate and the tragic tale of Getheren and Hode.","recentEvents":"The brothers Getheren and Hode vowed kemmering, but their vow was broken after Getheren's brother committed suicide, leading Getheren to flee northward.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Adjacent region"},{"location":"Shath Domain","relationship":"Historical location tied to the brothers' story"}]},{"name":"Pering Ice","aliases":["Pering Glacier"],"description":"A vast glacial sheet covering northern Karhide, contiguous with the Gobrin Ice of Orgoreyn during winter.","recentEvents":"Getheren traveled northward across the Ice, encountering a supernatural realm where the dead dwell.","relationships":[{"location":"Gobrin Ice","relationship":"Contiguous during winter"},{"location":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","relationship":"Site of Getheren's encounter with Hode"}]},{"name":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","aliases":["Blizzard Place"],"description":"A supernatural realm existing within the Pering Ice, where the dead who died in kemmering dwell eternally.","recentEvents":"Getheren met his deceased brother Hode here, who could not speak his name due to his death.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Located within the glacier"},{"location":"Shath Domain","relationship":"Linked to the brothers' tragic history"}]},{"name":"Gobrin Ice","description":"A glacial expanse in Orgoreyn, contiguous with the Pering Ice during winter storms.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a geographical counterpart to the Pering Ice, part of the frozen north.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Contiguous during winter"}]},{"name":"Shath Domain","aliases":["Hearth of Shath"],"description":"A Karhidish domain where the tragic tale of Getheren and Hode originated.","recentEvents":"The brothers' broken vow and Getheren's exile began here, leading to his journey north.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Storm-border","relationship":"Historical location tied to the brothers' story"}]},{"name":"Orgoreyn","aliases":["Karhide's neighbor"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Orgoreyn Political Tensions","description":"A rival state to Karhide, known for its harsh environment and political tensions.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai contemplates traveling here but hesitates due to potential difficulties returning to Karhide.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Adjacent rival state"}]},{"name":"Fastnesses","arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"A remote eastern region of Karhide containing the Foretellers, who hold significant cultural and prophetic influence.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai resolves to travel here to gather information about Karhide's political dynamics.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Eastern region"}]},{"name":"Grende","aliases":["Grende Region"],"description":"A region in northern Osnoriner, home to Charuthe.","recentEvents":"Herbor travels through the snows of Grende on his way to Charuthe to seek a foretelling for Berosty rem ir Ipe.","relationships":[{"location":"Charuthe","relationship":"Adjacent region"}]},{"name":"New Port","aliases":["New Port"],"description":"A coastal city serving as a departure point for caravans heading east.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai departs from here aboard a trade-caravan bound for the Pering Storm-border.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Storm-border","relationship":"Part of the caravan's route"}]},{"name":"Eskar Pass","aliases":["Eskar Pass"],"description":"A mountain pass through the Kargav range, critical for caravan travel.","recentEvents":"The caravan traverses this pass, encountering extreme weather and avalanches.","relationships":[{"location":"Kargav","relationship":"A key route through the mountain range"}]},{"name":"Ariskostor Fastness","aliases":["Ariskostor Fastness"],"description":"A remote castle-like structure perched on the Kargav's southern face.","recentEvents":"The driver describes it as a residence for the Old Men, inaccessible for most of the year.","relationships":[{"location":"Kargav","relationship":"Located on the mountain range"}]},{"name":"Otherhord","aliases":["Otherhord"],"arc":"Gethenian Cultural Exploration","description":"A secluded Fastness in a forested region, home to the Handdara cult.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai stays here to study the Foretellers' practices and their philosophy of nusuth.","relationships":[{"location":"Fastnesses","relationship":"A specific example of a Handdara retreat"}]},{"name":"Spreve","description":"Domain of the physician from Spreve, a region known for its medical expertise and connection to the Foretellers.","recentEvents":"The physician from Spreve entered the Foretelling circle during the session, interrupting the ritual with a demand for light.","relationships":[{"location":"Otherhord","relationship":"The physician's origin domain"}]},{"name":"Kuseben","aliases":["Kuseben"],"description":"A coastal town in Karhide where Estraven meets Ashe and attempts to flee exile.","recentEvents":"Estraven arrives in Kuseben after fleeing Erhenrang, meets Ashe, and tries to escape to Orgoreyn by sea.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Bordering region; Estraven's escape route"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Shelt Port","aliases":["Shelt"],"description":"A port city in Orgoreyn where Estraven is set ashore after being intercepted by patrol.","recentEvents":"Estraven is rescued by the Kuseben Patrol and landed here, leading to his detention in the Commensal Hospital.","relationships":[{"location":"Charisune Coastal Area Four","relationship":"Adjacent coastal region"}]},{"name":"Markets of South Mishnory","aliases":["South Mishnory Markets"],"description":"A bustling market hub in Mishnory where Estraven finds work as a landboat loader.","recentEvents":"Estraven works in the ice-houses and lodges on Fish Island, navigating Orgoreyn's social and political systems.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Central commercial district"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Fish Island","aliases":["Fish Island"],"description":"A crowded island near Mishnory's Markets where Estraven lodges with fellow workers.","recentEvents":"Estraven resides here while working in the ice-houses, enduring harsh conditions and social scrutiny.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Residential district"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Kunderer Embankment","aliases":["Kunderer Embankment"],"description":"A tree-lined area in Mishnory offering respite from the city's heat.","recentEvents":"Estraven retreats here to escape the oppressive summer heat of Mishnory.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Recreational area"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Charisune Coastal Area Four","aliases":["Charisune Coastal Area Four"],"description":"A coastal region in Orgoreyn housing the Commensal Hospital where Estraven is detained.","recentEvents":"Estraven is hospitalized here after a failed escape attempt, where he encounters the Inspector and physician.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Administrative district"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Sennethny","aliases":["Sennethny"],"description":"A location within the Twenty-fourth Commensality of Orgoreyn, tied to Estraven's hospital stay.","recentEvents":"Estraven is registered as a dependent in this commensality after his hospitalization.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Subdivision of the Great Commensality"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Osnoriner","aliases":["Osnoriner Region"],"description":"A region in Karhide known for its unique divorce practices and social customs.","recentEvents":"Discussed as a place where divorce exists but remarriage after divorce or death is prohibited.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of the Karhide region"}]},{"name":"Perunter","aliases":["Perunter Continent"],"description":"An Antarctic continent where incest between generations is reportedly permitted, though disputed.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a possible location with different social norms regarding incest.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Adjacent or nearby region"}]},{"name":"Gorinhering","aliases":["Gorinhering Clan-Hearth"],"description":"A Clan-Hearth on Karhide's Eastern coast, built on a hill above the Hodomin Ocean.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai resided here during the summer, interacting with locals and observing Karhidish culture.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of the Eastern coastal region"},{"location":"Hodomin Ocean","relationship":"Surrounded by the eternal fogs of this ocean"}]},{"name":"Ey River","description":"A glacier-fed border river between Karhide and Orgoreyn, marked by a bridge connecting Passerer and Siuwensin.","recentEvents":"A Karhidish foray raided Siuwensin, prompting Genly's journey into Orgoreyn.","relationships":[{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Karhidish village across the river"},{"location":"Siuwensin","relationship":"Orgota village across the river"}]},{"name":"Passerer","description":"A Karhidish village on the Karhide side of the Ey River bridge.","recentEvents":"A foray from Passerer raids Siuwensin, causing widespread destruction.","relationships":[{"location":"Ey River","relationship":"Located across the river from Siuwensin"},{"location":"Ovord Domain","relationship":"Alleged origin of foray guns"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent Commensal territory"}]},{"name":"Siuwensin","arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Orgoreyn Political Tensions","description":"An Orgota village on the Orgoreyn side of the Ey River bridge.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai and refugees are detained here after a raid, interrogated, and held in a storage-barn overnight.","relationships":[{"location":"Ey River","relationship":"Located across the river from Passerer"},{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Source of the raiding foray"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent inspection point"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Commensal Border-Station","description":"An Orgote border checkpoint where Genly obtained a permiso for travel.","recentEvents":"Processed Genly's entry into Orgoreyn after verifying his credentials.","relationships":[{"location":"Siuwensin","relationship":"Adjacent to the Commensal Transient-House"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Ovord Domain","aliases":["Ovord Domain"],"description":"A Commensal region accused of supplying foray guns to Passerer.","recentEvents":"Whispers suggest Ovord Domain's involvement in the Siuwensin raid via foray guns.","relationships":[{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Alleged supplier of foray weapons"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent Commensal territory"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Icefoot Lake","aliases":["Icefoot"],"description":"A frozen lake in Kerm Land where key events unfold.","recentEvents":"Young Estraven falls through the ice, is rescued by Therem of Stok, and later wounded during a hunt.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of Kerm Land"}]},{"name":"Ebos village","description":"A village on the north shore of Icefoot Lake.","recentEvents":"Estraven is taken here after being injured, then later the village sends people to retrieve Estraven's body.","relationships":[{"location":"Icefoot Lake","relationship":"Adjacent"}]},{"name":"Rotherer Fastness","description":"A remote fastness where Therem of Stok resides for a year.","recentEvents":"Therem indwells here after being exiled, later returning to Estre as its new lord.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of Kerm Land"}]},{"name":"Artisan School","aliases":["Royal Workshop Foundry"],"description":"A central institution in Karhide where technological and artistic craftsmanship is practiced.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai mentions the ship's components are stored here after landing on Horden Island.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Horden Island","description":"A remote island where Genly Ai first landed on Gethen, serving as a temporary base for his mission.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai's arrival and subsequent departure from the island were discussed during conversations in Mishnory.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Linked via transportation"}]},{"name":"Hall of the Thirty-Three","aliases":["Thirty-Three Hall"],"description":"The assembly chamber where Orgote political debates occur.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai spoke here without public audience; Obsle played a tape of the session for Estraven.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Central political venue"}]},{"name":"Plastics Factory","description":"Estraven's workplace where he produces transparent boxes.","recentEvents":"Estraven works here during the day, reflecting on his exile and the Envoy's mission.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Industrial district"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Central Bureau Radio","description":"The Orgote government's communication hub controlling information flow.","recentEvents":"Estraven notes its role in suppressing news about the Envoy.","relationships":[{"location":"Sarf","relationship":"Operated by the Sarf"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Commensal Public Kemmerhouses","description":"Public venues for communal sexual activities and performances.","recentEvents":"Slose opposes obscene plays here, advocating for moral reform.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Social gathering spaces"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Pyenefen Street","description":"A commercial street where Gaum approaches Estraven.","recentEvents":"Gaum attempts to seduce Estraven, revealing Sarf surveillance.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Urban thoroughfare"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"}],"arcs":[{"name":"Genly Ai's Mission and Orgoreyn Political Tensions","status":"active","characters":["Genly Ai","Obsle","Shusgis","Sarf","Yegey"],"summary":"Genly's mission faces escalating political resistance as Orgoreyn's Thirty-Three Commensals remain divided. The Sarf's control over communications stifles public discourse, and Obsle's cautious diplomacy risks Genly's safety. The Envoy's inability to secure radio contact with his ship heightens the stakes of his isolation."},{"name":"Estraven's Exile and Cross-National Political Struggles","status":"active","characters":["Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","Obsle","Gaum","Sarf","Tibe"],"summary":"Estraven's efforts to rally Orgoreyn's political factions falter as fear and factionalism dominate. His clandestine interactions with Genly and the Sarf's pervasive surveillance underscore his precarious position, while the Commensals' reluctance to act leaves him powerless to protect the Envoy."},{"name":"Gethenian Cultural Exploration","status":"dormant","characters":["Genly Ai","Commensals","Foretellers"],"summary":"Genly's attempts to engage with Gethenian culture are sidelined by political intrigue, though his discussions about the Ekumen's philosophy persist. The cultural arc temporarily recedes as political tensions dominate, though its underlying themes of alienation and communication remain unresolved."}],"summary":"Estraven observes political tensions in Mishnory as the Orgote Thirty-Three debates the Envoy's mission, while fearing for Genly Ai's safety. The Sarf's control over communications stifles public discourse, and Estraven struggles to convince officials to act, realizing their fear of the unknown may doom the Envoy's efforts."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":15,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Genly Ai","aliases":["Mr. Ai","the Envoy"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"The Ekumen's Envoy to Karhide, struggling with the political and psychological complexities of his mission.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Former contact; Estraven is now the King’s Ear"},{"character":"King Argaven XV","relationship":"The monarch he is attempting to persuade to join the Ekumen"}],"recentEvents":"Spoke in the Hall of the Thirty-Three, faced interruptions and skepticism from Domination faction members."},{"name":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","aliases":["The King’s Ear","Lord Estraven"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A nobleman from the Domain of Estre, known for his complex relationship with Genly Ai and his role in ending the feud between Estre and Stok.","relationships":[{"character":"King Argaven XV","relationship":"Formerly the king's closest confidant and advisor"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Allied through covert communication and financial support"},{"character":"Foreth rem ir Osboth","relationship":"Former kemmering (male companion)"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed the Envoy's safety with Estraven, hesitated to publicize his mission due to Sarf control."},{"name":"King Argaven XV","aliases":["the king"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Royal House","description":"The paranoid and volatile ruler of Karhide, suspicious of foreign influence and internal dissent.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Formerly his most trusted advisor, now exiled"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"The Envoy whose mission he resists and interrogates"}],"recentEvents":"Child's birth and death, political speculation about succession"},{"name":"Pemmer Harge rem ir Tibe","aliases":["the king’s cousin"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The king’s cousin and a member of the upper chamber, known for his rivalry with Estraven.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Rival and political adversary"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Interacted during the dinner conversation"}],"recentEvents":"Featured in news about Karhide’s territorial claims in the Sinoth Valley"},{"name":"servant","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"1. A Parade in Erhenrang","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Karhidish servant who left after the meal.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Departed to their home after the meal, as Karhiders do not employ bonded labor."},{"name":"Getheren","aliases":["Ennoch"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Brother who survived the exile and journey to the Ice, met his brother Hode in the Place Inside the Blizzard.","relationships":[{"character":"Hode","relationship":"Brother"}],"recentEvents":"Traveled to the Pering Ice, encountered Hode, died after returning to Shath and revealing his identity."},{"name":"Hode","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","description":"Getheren's brother who committed suicide after being exiled, now resides in the Place Inside the Blizzard.","relationships":[{"character":"Getheren","relationship":"Brother"}],"recentEvents":"Died by suicide, appeared to Getheren in the Place Inside the Blizzard as a white, lifeless figure."},{"name":"the traveler","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Carried Getheren's message back to Shath, confirming the domain's recovery after Getheren's death.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received Getheren's final message and relayed it to Shath, contributing to the domain's restoration."},{"name":"Lord Berosty rem ir Ipe","aliases":["Ashe Berosty rem ir Ipe"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"4. The Nineteenth Day","currentLocation":"Grende","description":"A nobleman who sought a Foretelling about his death and later killed his kemmering Herbor before dying by suicide.","relationships":[{"character":"Herbor of the Geganner clan","relationship":"kemmering"}],"recentEvents":"Received a Foretelling about his death, killed Herbor, and hanged himself on Odstreth."},{"name":"Herbor of the Geganner clan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"4. The Nineteenth Day","currentLocation":"Grende","description":"A poor man who sought a Foretelling to save his kemmering Berosty rem ir Ipe.","relationships":[{"character":"Lord Berosty rem ir Ipe","relationship":"kemmering"}],"recentEvents":"Sought a Foretelling, was killed by Berosty, and died from the injury."},{"name":"Weaver Odren","aliases":["The Weaver","the Weaver","Faxe"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Otherhord","description":"A Foreteller and the Weaver of the group, known for his role in the Foretelling sessions.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Envoy and seeker of answers"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted the Foretelling session for Genly Ai, where he answered the question about Gethen's membership in the Ekumen."},{"name":"Goss","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Otherhord","description":"A young Indweller who guides Genly Ai to the Fastness of Otherhord.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Guide and companion"}],"recentEvents":"Led Genly Ai to Otherhord and engaged in conversation about the Handdara"},{"name":"the driver","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"on the caravan","description":"The driver of the landboats guiding the caravan through the Kargav.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Guided the caravan and shared stories about the Fastnesses"},{"name":"the physician from Spreve","aliases":["the physician"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Otherhord","description":"A physician from Spreve who entered the circle during the Foretelling session.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Entered the circle during the Foretelling session, contributing to the disruption of the session."},{"name":"the cook","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"6. One Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A servant who wakes Therem Harth","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Helped Therem escape by providing food"},{"name":"the fisherman","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"6. One Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A fisherman who initially refused to help Therem","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Refused to assist Therem but later led to his capture"},{"name":"The Inspector","aliases":["Inspector"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Commensal Border-Station","description":"A government official handling refugee interrogations and border controls.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in context of bureaucratic oversight"},{"name":"Commensal Yegey","aliases":["Yegey"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Host at the lunch gathering, curious about the Ekumen.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Maintains dependent relationship"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Host"}],"recentEvents":"Opposed the blockade of grain-exports to Karhide during the Hall session."},{"name":"Commensal Obsle","aliases":["Obsle"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Commensal with political tensions regarding Estraven","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Politically entangled"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Interrogator"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed the Envoy's radio contact with the Star Ship, hesitated due to Sarf control."},{"name":"Foreth rem ir Osboth","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"8. Another Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Orgny Fastness","description":"Estraven's former kemmering, now an Indweller at Orgny Fastness.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Debt owed for aiding Estraven"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Genly Ai money to deliver to Estraven, expressing hope for his survival."},{"name":"the baby","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"8. Another Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"","relationships":[]},{"name":"Arek of Estre","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The heir of the Domain of Estre, who was killed by a Stok warrior during a feud between the two domains.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Killed by a Stok warrior while traveling through the thore-forest, his body left to be eaten by wild beasts."},{"name":"The murderer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Stok warrior who killed Arek of Estre during the feud between the domains.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Stabbed Arek of Estre to death and left his body to be eaten by wild beasts."},{"name":"The men from Stok","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A group of Stok warriors who disobeyed their lord's orders and left Arek of Estre's body to be eaten by wild beasts.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Disobeyed their lord's command to bury Arek of Estre, leading to their banishment."},{"name":"Lord Sorve","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The lord of the Domain of Estre who died, leaving his heir Therem to inherit the domain.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Died, leading to Therem becoming Lord of Estre and ending the feud with Stok."},{"name":"The old lord","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Estre","description":"The lord of the Domain of Estre who adopted the child of Arek of Estre as his heir.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Adopted the child of Arek of Estre and named him Therem, who later became Lord of Estre."},{"name":"The people from Ebos village","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Residents of Ebos village who helped Therem of Stok after he was wounded.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Carried Therem of Stok back to Estre after he was wounded in the thore-forest."},{"name":"Mersen","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Karhidish agent suspected of espionage.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Suspected informant"},{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Suspected of espionage"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed as a spy for Tibe, target of political suspicion"},{"name":"Gaum","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A member of the Sarf who attempted to seduce Estraven during kemmer.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Curious observer"},{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Politically adversarial"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to seduce Estraven during kemmer, failed due to Estraven's abstinence."},{"name":"Humery","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Fat old man in purple, skeptical of interstellar trade.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Expressed disgust at interstellar travel"},{"name":"Slose","aliases":["Commensal Slose"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A Commensal and mystic who interpreted the Envoy's mission as a spiritual event.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Advocate for Ekumen"}],"recentEvents":"Led a committee to suppress obscene plays, interpreted the Envoy's mission as a spiritual event."},{"name":"The fat old man in purple","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Skeptical diner at the lunch gathering.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Expressed disgust at interstellar travel"},{"name":"Shusgis","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Commensal with knowledge of Orgoreyn's bureaucracy","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Provided information about Sarf and political factions"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed Orgoreyn's secret police, Estraven's status, and political factions"},{"name":"Csl. Ithepen of the Eynyen District","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A member of the Thirty-Three who proposed inviting the Star Ship to Orgoreyn.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Proposed to Obsle to invite the Star Ship to Orgoreyn, but the plan was rejected."},{"name":"Alshel","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Presiding officer in the Hall of the Thirty-Three during the Envoy's speech.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Presided over the session where the Envoy spoke about the Star Ship."},{"name":"Kaharosile","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A member of the Domination faction who interrupted the Envoy's speech with accusations.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Interrupted the session with accusations against the Envoy, claiming he was a Karhidish agent."},{"name":"Meshe","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"12. On Time and Darkness","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A High Priest whose sayings form the Yomesh Canon, central to the philosophical and cosmological teachings of Gethen.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Delivered teachings on time, darkness, and the nature of existence through parables and prophecies."},{"name":"Tuhulme","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"12. On Time and Darkness","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The author of the Sayings attributed to Meshe, a figure in Gethen's religious and philosophical history.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Compiled the Sayings of Meshe into the Yomesh Canon."},{"name":"The poor man of Sheney","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"12. On Time and Darkness","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A character in a parable about seeking treasure and the consequences of greed.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Discovered a buried treasure but faced a grim fate foretold by Meshe."},{"name":"The Lord of Shorth","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"12. On Time and Darkness","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A ruler referenced in Meshe's parable about the nature of time and vision.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in Meshe's mystical vision of the universe's expansion."}],"locations":[{"name":"Erhenrang","aliases":["Capital City","City of Karhide","Arch of the River Gate","New Road and River Port","Island","Genly's Lodgings","Winter","Planet Winter","Gethen","Old Bridge","Ancient Bridge"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"The capital city of Karhide, known for its grand architecture and political significance. A monumental structure completed to enhance Erhenrang's trade and infrastructure. A communal living space for foreigners in Erhenrang, where Genly Ai resides. The icy planet where Karhide is located, with extreme seasonal variations. A historic bridge over the river, noted for its arches and traditional construction methods.","recentEvents":"Hosted a parade celebrating the completion of the Arch of the River Gate, where Genly Ai interacts with key figures like King Argaven XV and Therem Harth rem ir Estraven.; Central to the parade, with the king and masons participating in its final assembly.; Where Genly Ai reflects on his isolation and observes local customs.; Setting for the entire narrative, with Genly Ai navigating its harsh climate and politics.; Mentioned as a reference point for the arch's mortar techniques.","relationships":[{"location":"Royal House","relationship":"Contains the royal residence and administrative center"},{"location":"Palace of Erhenrang","relationship":"Part of the city's walled inner complex"}]},{"name":"Royal House","aliases":["King's Residence","Royal Palace"],"arc":"Estraven's Exile and Cross-National Political Struggles","description":"The fortified palace complex housing the king and key political figures.","recentEvents":"Served as the backdrop for the royal procession and the keystone-laying ceremony.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Central structure within the city"},{"location":"King's House","relationship":"Part of the same complex"}]},{"name":"Corner Red Dwelling","aliases":["Estraven's Home"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"A historic residence of Therem Harth rem ir Estraven, symbolizing his political influence.","recentEvents":"Where Genly Ai is invited for dinner, revealing shifting power dynamics.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Located within the city's walls"}]},{"name":"Sess Embankment","aliases":["River Embankment"],"description":"A public area along the river where crowds gather for events.","recentEvents":"Where the parade crowd watches the keystone ceremony and the king's procession.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Key public space in the city"}],"parentLocation":"Erhenrang"},{"name":"Karhide","aliases":["Nation of Karhide"],"arc":"Estraven's Exile and Cross-National Political Struggles","description":"A politically complex nation on Winter, ruled by King Argaven XV.","recentEvents":"Central to the narrative, with Genly Ai navigating its social and political structures.","relationships":[{"location":"Winter","relationship":"Nation on the planet"}]},{"name":"North Fall","aliases":["High North Fall"],"description":"A remote, snowbound region bordering Karhide and Orgoreyn, marked by harsh climate and political tension.","recentEvents":"Estraven discusses aiding Karhidish farmers displaced from the Sinoth Valley, risking political fallout with the king.","relationships":[{"location":"Sassinoth Valley","relationship":"Adjacent border region contested by Karhide and Orgoreyn"},{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of Karhide's northern territory"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Sassinoth Valley","aliases":["Sinoth Valley"],"arc":"Estraven's Political Maneuvering and Border Dispute (Historical Context)","description":"A valley trapped in political conflict between Karhide and Orgoreyn, where the narrative's central tensions unfold.","recentEvents":"Karhidish farmers launched a foray here, burning an Orgota village and dumping bodies into the Ey River.","relationships":[{"location":"North Fall","relationship":"Part of the contested border region"},{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Historically inhabited by Orgoreyn settlers"},{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Site of political resistance to the Envoy's mission"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Remny Tower","description":"A tower in Erhenrang where gongs mark the time, symbolizing the city's rigid temporal structure.","recentEvents":"Estraven and Genly Ai hear the gongs signaling midnight as their conversation concludes.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Part of the city's infrastructure"}],"parentLocation":"Erhenrang"},{"name":"Pering Storm-border","aliases":["Storm-border"],"description":"A region in northern Karhide bordering the Pering Ice, known for its harsh climate and the tragic tale of Getheren and Hode.","recentEvents":"The brothers Getheren and Hode vowed kemmering, but their vow was broken after Getheren's brother committed suicide, leading Getheren to flee northward.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Adjacent region"},{"location":"Shath Domain","relationship":"Historical location tied to the brothers' story"}]},{"name":"Pering Ice","aliases":["Pering Glacier"],"description":"A vast glacial sheet covering northern Karhide, contiguous with the Gobrin Ice of Orgoreyn during winter.","recentEvents":"Getheren traveled northward across the Ice, encountering a supernatural realm where the dead dwell.","relationships":[{"location":"Gobrin Ice","relationship":"Contiguous during winter"},{"location":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","relationship":"Site of Getheren's encounter with Hode"}]},{"name":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","aliases":["Blizzard Place"],"description":"A supernatural realm existing within the Pering Ice, where the dead who died in kemmering dwell eternally.","recentEvents":"Getheren met his deceased brother Hode here, who could not speak his name due to his death.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Located within the glacier"},{"location":"Shath Domain","relationship":"Linked to the brothers' tragic history"}],"parentLocation":"Pering Ice"},{"name":"Gobrin Ice","description":"A glacial expanse in Orgoreyn, contiguous with the Pering Ice during winter storms.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a geographical counterpart to the Pering Ice, part of the frozen north.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Contiguous during winter"}]},{"name":"Shath Domain","aliases":["Hearth of Shath"],"description":"A Karhidish domain where the tragic tale of Getheren and Hode originated.","recentEvents":"The brothers' broken vow and Getheren's exile began here, leading to his journey north.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Storm-border","relationship":"Historical location tied to the brothers' story"}]},{"name":"Orgoreyn","aliases":["Karhide's neighbor"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Karhide-Orgoreyn Temporal Tensions","description":"A rival state to Karhide, known for its harsh environment and political tensions.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai contemplates traveling here but hesitates due to potential difficulties returning to Karhide.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Adjacent rival state"}]},{"name":"Fastnesses","arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"A remote eastern region of Karhide containing the Foretellers, who hold significant cultural and prophetic influence.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai resolves to travel here to gather information about Karhide's political dynamics.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Eastern region"}]},{"name":"Grende","aliases":["Grende Region"],"description":"A region in northern Osnoriner, home to Charuthe.","recentEvents":"Herbor travels through the snows of Grende on his way to Charuthe to seek a foretelling for Berosty rem ir Ipe.","relationships":[{"location":"Charuthe","relationship":"Adjacent region"}]},{"name":"New Port","aliases":["New Port"],"description":"A coastal city serving as a departure point for caravans heading east.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai departs from here aboard a trade-caravan bound for the Pering Storm-border.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Storm-border","relationship":"Part of the caravan's route"}]},{"name":"Eskar Pass","aliases":["Eskar Pass"],"description":"A mountain pass through the Kargav range, critical for caravan travel.","recentEvents":"The caravan traverses this pass, encountering extreme weather and avalanches.","relationships":[{"location":"Kargav","relationship":"A key route through the mountain range"}]},{"name":"Ariskostor Fastness","aliases":["Ariskostor Fastness"],"description":"A remote castle-like structure perched on the Kargav's southern face.","recentEvents":"The driver describes it as a residence for the Old Men, inaccessible for most of the year.","relationships":[{"location":"Kargav","relationship":"Located on the mountain range"}]},{"name":"Otherhord","aliases":["Otherhord"],"arc":"Gethenian Cultural Exploration","description":"A secluded Fastness in a forested region, home to the Handdara cult.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai stays here to study the Foretellers' practices and their philosophy of nusuth.","relationships":[{"location":"Fastnesses","relationship":"A specific example of a Handdara retreat"}]},{"name":"Spreve","description":"Domain of the physician from Spreve, a region known for its medical expertise and connection to the Foretellers.","recentEvents":"The physician from Spreve entered the Foretelling circle during the session, interrupting the ritual with a demand for light.","relationships":[{"location":"Otherhord","relationship":"The physician's origin domain"}]},{"name":"Kuseben","aliases":["Kuseben"],"description":"A coastal town in Karhide where Estraven meets Ashe and attempts to flee exile.","recentEvents":"Estraven arrives in Kuseben after fleeing Erhenrang, meets Ashe, and tries to escape to Orgoreyn by sea.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Bordering region; Estraven's escape route"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Shelt Port","aliases":["Shelt"],"description":"A port city in Orgoreyn where Estraven is set ashore after being intercepted by patrol.","recentEvents":"Estraven is rescued by the Kuseben Patrol and landed here, leading to his detention in the Commensal Hospital.","relationships":[{"location":"Charisune Coastal Area Four","relationship":"Adjacent coastal region"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Markets of South Mishnory","aliases":["South Mishnory Markets"],"description":"A bustling market hub in Mishnory where Estraven finds work as a landboat loader.","recentEvents":"Estraven works in the ice-houses and lodges on Fish Island, navigating Orgoreyn's social and political systems.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Central commercial district"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Fish Island","aliases":["Fish Island"],"description":"A crowded island near Mishnory's Markets where Estraven lodges with fellow workers.","recentEvents":"Estraven resides here while working in the ice-houses, enduring harsh conditions and social scrutiny.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Residential district"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Kunderer Embankment","aliases":["Kunderer Embankment"],"description":"A tree-lined area in Mishnory offering respite from the city's heat.","recentEvents":"Estraven retreats here to escape the oppressive summer heat of Mishnory.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Recreational area"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Charisune Coastal Area Four","aliases":["Charisune Coastal Area Four"],"description":"A coastal region in Orgoreyn housing the Commensal Hospital where Estraven is detained.","recentEvents":"Estraven is hospitalized here after a failed escape attempt, where he encounters the Inspector and physician.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Administrative district"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Sennethny","aliases":["Sennethny"],"description":"A location within the Twenty-fourth Commensality of Orgoreyn, tied to Estraven's hospital stay.","recentEvents":"Estraven is registered as a dependent in this commensality after his hospitalization.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Subdivision of the Great Commensality"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Osnoriner","aliases":["Osnoriner Region"],"description":"A region in Karhide known for its unique divorce practices and social customs.","recentEvents":"Discussed as a place where divorce exists but remarriage after divorce or death is prohibited.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of the Karhide region"}]},{"name":"Perunter","aliases":["Perunter Continent"],"description":"An Antarctic continent where incest between generations is reportedly permitted, though disputed.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a possible location with different social norms regarding incest.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Adjacent or nearby region"}]},{"name":"Gorinhering","aliases":["Gorinhering Clan-Hearth"],"description":"A Clan-Hearth on Karhide's Eastern coast, built on a hill above the Hodomin Ocean.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai resided here during the summer, interacting with locals and observing Karhidish culture.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of the Eastern coastal region"},{"location":"Hodomin Ocean","relationship":"Surrounded by the eternal fogs of this ocean"}]},{"name":"Ey River","description":"A glacier-fed border river between Karhide and Orgoreyn, marked by a bridge connecting Passerer and Siuwensin.","recentEvents":"A Karhidish foray raided Siuwensin, prompting Genly's journey into Orgoreyn.","relationships":[{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Karhidish village across the river"},{"location":"Siuwensin","relationship":"Orgota village across the river"}]},{"name":"Passerer","description":"A Karhidish village on the Karhide side of the Ey River bridge.","recentEvents":"A foray from Passerer raids Siuwensin, causing widespread destruction.","relationships":[{"location":"Ey River","relationship":"Located across the river from Siuwensin"},{"location":"Ovord Domain","relationship":"Alleged origin of foray guns"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent Commensal territory"}]},{"name":"Siuwensin","arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Orgoreyn Political Tensions","description":"An Orgota village on the Orgoreyn side of the Ey River bridge.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai and refugees are detained here after a raid, interrogated, and held in a storage-barn overnight.","relationships":[{"location":"Ey River","relationship":"Located across the river from Passerer"},{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Source of the raiding foray"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent inspection point"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Commensal Border-Station","description":"An Orgote border checkpoint where Genly obtained a permiso for travel.","recentEvents":"Processed Genly's entry into Orgoreyn after verifying his credentials.","relationships":[{"location":"Siuwensin","relationship":"Adjacent to the Commensal Transient-House"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Ovord Domain","aliases":["Ovord Domain"],"description":"A Commensal region accused of supplying foray guns to Passerer.","recentEvents":"Whispers suggest Ovord Domain's involvement in the Siuwensin raid via foray guns.","relationships":[{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Alleged supplier of foray weapons"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent Commensal territory"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Icefoot Lake","aliases":["Icefoot"],"description":"A frozen lake in Kerm Land where key events unfold.","recentEvents":"Young Estraven falls through the ice, is rescued by Therem of Stok, and later wounded during a hunt.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of Kerm Land"}]},{"name":"Ebos village","description":"A village on the north shore of Icefoot Lake.","recentEvents":"Estraven is taken here after being injured, then later the village sends people to retrieve Estraven's body.","relationships":[{"location":"Icefoot Lake","relationship":"Adjacent"}],"parentLocation":"Icefoot Lake"},{"name":"Rotherer Fastness","description":"A remote fastness where Therem of Stok resides for a year.","recentEvents":"Therem indwells here after being exiled, later returning to Estre as its new lord.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of Kerm Land"}]},{"name":"Artisan School","aliases":["Royal Workshop Foundry"],"description":"A central institution in Karhide where technological and artistic craftsmanship is practiced.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai mentions the ship's components are stored here after landing on Horden Island.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Horden Island","description":"A remote island where Genly Ai first landed on Gethen, serving as a temporary base for his mission.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai's arrival and subsequent departure from the island were discussed during conversations in Mishnory.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Linked via transportation"}]},{"name":"Hall of the Thirty-Three","aliases":["Thirty-Three Hall"],"description":"The assembly chamber where Orgote political debates occur.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai spoke here without public audience; Obsle played a tape of the session for Estraven.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Central political venue"}]},{"name":"Plastics Factory","description":"Estraven's workplace where he produces transparent boxes.","recentEvents":"Estraven works here during the day, reflecting on his exile and the Envoy's mission.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Industrial district"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Central Bureau Radio","description":"The Orgote government's communication hub controlling information flow.","recentEvents":"Estraven notes its role in suppressing news about the Envoy.","relationships":[{"location":"Sarf","relationship":"Operated by the Sarf"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Commensal Public Kemmerhouses","description":"Public venues for communal sexual activities and performances.","recentEvents":"Slose opposes obscene plays here, advocating for moral reform.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Social gathering spaces"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Pyenefen Street","description":"A commercial street where Gaum approaches Estraven.","recentEvents":"Gaum attempts to seduce Estraven, revealing Sarf surveillance.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Urban thoroughfare"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Meshe","aliases":["Center of Time"],"description":"A mystical location central to the narrative's philosophical themes, where Meshe perceives all time and existence simultaneously.","recentEvents":"Meshe's teachings about the Center of Time are recounted, revealing his prophetic visions of past, present, and future events.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Meshe is a spiritual figure associated with Karhide's cosmology"}],"arc":"Gethenian Cultural Exploration"},{"name":"Tuerresh","description":"A region where the poor man of Sheney discovers a buried treasure, fulfilling Meshe's prophecy.","recentEvents":"The poor man excavates and finds ancient jewels, but Meshe foresees their eventual destruction and his own death.","relationships":[{"location":"Sheney","relationship":"Tuerresh is linked to the village of Sheney through the poor man's journey"}]},{"name":"Ornen Forest","description":"A vast, ancient forest housing a hemmen-tree with a secret leaf hidden in its darkness.","recentEvents":"Meshe plucks the hidden leaf from the tree, symbolizing the revelation of concealed truths.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"The forest is part of Karhide's geography"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Genly Ai's Mission and Karhide-Orgoreyn Temporal Tensions","status":"active","characters":["Genly Ai","Obsle","Shusgis","Sarf","Yegey"],"summary":"Genly's mission faces escalating political resistance as Orgoreyn's Thirty-Three Commensals remain divided. The Sarf's control over communications stifles public discourse, and Obsle's cautious diplomacy risks Genly's safety. The Envoy's inability to secure radio contact with his ship heightens the stakes of his isolation."},{"name":"Estraven's Exile and Cross-National Political Struggles","status":"active","characters":["Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","Obsle","Gaum","Sarf","Tibe"],"summary":"Estraven's efforts to rally Orgoreyn's political factions falter as fear and factionalism dominate. His clandestine interactions with Genly and the Sarf's pervasive surveillance underscore his precarious position, while the Commensals' reluctance to act leaves him powerless to protect the Envoy."},{"name":"Gethenian Cultural Exploration","status":"active","characters":["Genly Ai","Therem Harth rem ir Estraven"],"summary":"The chapter's philosophical revelations about Meshe and the Center of Time reframe Genly's cultural misunderstandings, suggesting Gethenian existence transcends linear time. The hemmen-tree metaphor and Meshe's 'Eye' challenge Genly's perception of Gethenian identity, reigniting the cultural exploration arc with new metaphysical dimensions."}],"summary":"Genly Ai and Estraven remain in Mishnory, navigating political tensions with the Karhidans. The chapter explores Meshe's mystical visions of time and fate, including prophecies about Tuerresh's treasure and the Ornen Forest's hidden leaf. Philosophical themes about the nature of time, darkness, and cosmic unity deepen the narrative's existential undertones."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":16,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Genly Ai","aliases":["Mr. Ai","the Envoy"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"The Ekumen's Envoy to Karhide, struggling with the political and psychological complexities of his mission.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Former contact; Estraven is now the King’s Ear"},{"character":"King Argaven XV","relationship":"The monarch he is attempting to persuade to join the Ekumen"}],"recentEvents":"Spoke in the Hall of the Thirty-Three, faced interruptions and skepticism from Domination faction members."},{"name":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","aliases":["The King’s Ear","Lord Estraven"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A nobleman from the Domain of Estre, known for his complex relationship with Genly Ai and his role in ending the feud between Estre and Stok.","relationships":[{"character":"King Argaven XV","relationship":"Formerly the king's closest confidant and advisor"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Allied through covert communication and financial support"},{"character":"Foreth rem ir Osboth","relationship":"Former kemmering (male companion)"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed the Envoy's safety with Estraven, hesitated to publicize his mission due to Sarf control."},{"name":"King Argaven XV","aliases":["the king"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Royal House","description":"The paranoid and volatile ruler of Karhide, suspicious of foreign influence and internal dissent.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Formerly his most trusted advisor, now exiled"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"The Envoy whose mission he resists and interrogates"}],"recentEvents":"Child's birth and death, political speculation about succession"},{"name":"Pemmer Harge rem ir Tibe","aliases":["the king’s cousin"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The king’s cousin and a member of the upper chamber, known for his rivalry with Estraven.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Rival and political adversary"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Interacted during the dinner conversation"}],"recentEvents":"Featured in news about Karhide’s territorial claims in the Sinoth Valley"},{"name":"servant","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"1. A Parade in Erhenrang","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Karhidish servant who left after the meal.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Departed to their home after the meal, as Karhiders do not employ bonded labor."},{"name":"Getheren","aliases":["Ennoch"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Brother who survived the exile and journey to the Ice, met his brother Hode in the Place Inside the Blizzard.","relationships":[{"character":"Hode","relationship":"Brother"}],"recentEvents":"Traveled to the Pering Ice, encountered Hode, died after returning to Shath and revealing his identity."},{"name":"Hode","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","description":"Getheren's brother who committed suicide after being exiled, now resides in the Place Inside the Blizzard.","relationships":[{"character":"Getheren","relationship":"Brother"}],"recentEvents":"Died by suicide, appeared to Getheren in the Place Inside the Blizzard as a white, lifeless figure."},{"name":"the traveler","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Carried Getheren's message back to Shath, confirming the domain's recovery after Getheren's death.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received Getheren's final message and relayed it to Shath, contributing to the domain's restoration."},{"name":"Lord Berosty rem ir Ipe","aliases":["Ashe Berosty rem ir Ipe"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"4. The Nineteenth Day","currentLocation":"Grende","description":"A nobleman who sought a Foretelling about his death and later killed his kemmering Herbor before dying by suicide.","relationships":[{"character":"Herbor of the Geganner clan","relationship":"kemmering"}],"recentEvents":"Received a Foretelling about his death, killed Herbor, and hanged himself on Odstreth."},{"name":"Herbor of the Geganner clan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"4. The Nineteenth Day","currentLocation":"Grende","description":"A poor man who sought a Foretelling to save his kemmering Berosty rem ir Ipe.","relationships":[{"character":"Lord Berosty rem ir Ipe","relationship":"kemmering"}],"recentEvents":"Sought a Foretelling, was killed by Berosty, and died from the injury."},{"name":"Weaver Odren","aliases":["The Weaver","the Weaver","Faxe"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"13. Down on the Farm","currentLocation":"Pulefen Commensality Third Voluntary Farm & Resettlement Agency","description":"A Foreteller and the Weaver of the group, known for his role in the Foretelling sessions.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Envoy and seeker of answers"},{"character":"the Inspector","relationship":"Aide"}],"recentEvents":"Administered drug examinations to Genly Ai and other prisoners."},{"name":"Goss","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Otherhord","description":"A young Indweller who guides Genly Ai to the Fastness of Otherhord.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Guide and companion"}],"recentEvents":"Led Genly Ai to Otherhord and engaged in conversation about the Handdara"},{"name":"the driver","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"on the caravan","description":"The driver of the landboats guiding the caravan through the Kargav.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Guided the caravan and shared stories about the Fastnesses"},{"name":"the physician from Spreve","aliases":["the physician"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Otherhord","description":"A physician from Spreve who entered the circle during the Foretelling session.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Entered the circle during the Foretelling session, contributing to the disruption of the session."},{"name":"the cook","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"6. One Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A servant who wakes Therem Harth","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem 