ionships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Debt owed for aiding Estraven"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Genly Ai money to deliver to Estraven, expressing hope for his survival."},{"name":"the baby","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"8. Another Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"","relationships":[]},{"name":"Arek of Estre","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The heir of the Domain of Estre, who was killed by a Stok warrior during a feud between the two domains.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Killed by a Stok warrior while traveling through the thore-forest, his body left to be eaten by wild beasts."},{"name":"The murderer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Stok warrior who killed Arek of Estre during the feud between the domains.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Stabbed Arek of Estre to death and left his body to be eaten by wild beasts."},{"name":"The men from Stok","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A group of Stok warriors who disobeyed their lord's orders and left Arek of Estre's body to be eaten by wild beasts.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Disobeyed their lord's command to bury Arek of Estre, leading to their banishment."},{"name":"Lord Sorve","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The lord of the Domain of Estre who died, leaving his heir Therem to inherit the domain.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Died, leading to Therem becoming Lord of Estre and ending the feud with Stok."},{"name":"The old lord","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Estre","description":"The lord of the Domain of Estre who adopted the child of Arek of Estre as his heir.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Adopted the child of Arek of Estre and named him Therem, who later became Lord of Estre."},{"name":"The people from Ebos village","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Residents of Ebos village who helped Therem of Stok after he was wounded.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Carried Therem of Stok back to Estre after he was wounded in the thore-forest."},{"name":"Mersen","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Karhidish agent suspected of espionage.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Suspected informant"},{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Suspected of espionage"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed as a spy for Tibe, target of political suspicion"},{"name":"Gaum","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A member of the Sarf who attempted to seduce Estraven during kemmer.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Curious observer"},{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Politically adversarial"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to seduce Estraven during kemmer, failed due to Estraven's abstinence."},{"name":"Humery","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Fat old man in purple, skeptical of interstellar trade.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Expressed disgust at interstellar travel"},{"name":"Slose","aliases":["Commensal Slose"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A Commensal and mystic who interpreted the Envoy's mission as a spiritual event.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Advocate for Ekumen"}],"recentEvents":"Led a committee to suppress obscene plays, interpreted the Envoy's mission as a spiritual event."},{"name":"The fat old man in purple","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Skeptical diner at the lunch gathering.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Expressed disgust at interstellar travel"},{"name":"Shusgis","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Commensal with knowledge of Orgoreyn's bureaucracy","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Provided information about Sarf and political factions"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed Orgoreyn's secret police, Estraven's status, and political factions"},{"name":"Csl. Ithepen of the Eynyen District","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A member of the Thirty-Three who proposed inviting the Star Ship to Orgoreyn.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Proposed to Obsle to invite the Star Ship to Orgoreyn, but the plan was rejected."},{"name":"Alshel","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Presiding officer in the Hall of the Thirty-Three during the Envoy's speech.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Presided over the session where the Envoy spoke about the Star Ship."},{"name":"Kaharosile","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A member of the Domination faction who interrupted the Envoy's speech with accusations.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Interrupted the session with accusations against the Envoy, claiming he was a Karhidish agent."},{"name":"Meshe","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"12. On Time and Darkness","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A High Priest whose sayings form the Yomesh Canon, central to the philosophical and cosmological teachings of Gethen.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Delivered teachings on time, darkness, and the nature of existence through parables and prophecies."},{"name":"Tuhulme","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"12. On Time and Darkness","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The author of the Sayings attributed to Meshe, a figure in Gethen's religious and philosophical history.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Compiled the Sayings of Meshe into the Yomesh Canon."},{"name":"The poor man of Sheney","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"12. On Time and Darkness","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A character in a parable about seeking treasure and the consequences of greed.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Discovered a buried treasure but faced a grim fate foretold by Meshe."},{"name":"The Lord of Shorth","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"12. On Time and Darkness","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A ruler referenced in Meshe's parable about the nature of time and vision.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in Meshe's mystical vision of the universe's expansion."},{"name":"the old man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"13. Down on the Farm","currentLocation":"Pulefen Commensality Third Voluntary Farm & Resettlement Agency","description":"A prisoner in the caravan truck recognized for being least resistant to cold.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Lived in the dormitory with Genly Ai and the man with a bad cough."},{"name":"the man with a bad cough","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"13. Down on the Farm","currentLocation":"Pulefen Commensality Third Voluntary Farm & Resettlement Agency","description":"A prisoner in the caravan truck recognized for being least resistant to cold.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Survived the caravan journey and was assigned to the farm labor camp."},{"name":"the girl","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"13. Down on the Farm","currentLocation":"Pulefen Commensality Third Voluntary Farm & Resettlement Agency","description":"An Orgota woman in kemmer who approached Genly Ai during the caravan journey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Attempted to seek solace from Genly Ai during the caravan journey."},{"name":"Asra","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"13. Down on the Farm","currentLocation":"Pulefen Commensality Third Voluntary Farm & Resettlement Agency","description":"A former carpenter imprisoned at the farm, known for his storytelling and eventual death from illness.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Prisoner companion"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in conversations with Genly Ai about his past, died after falling into a coma."},{"name":"the guards","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"13. Down on the Farm","currentLocation":"Pulefen Commensality Third Voluntary Farm & Resettlement Agency","description":"Probationary prisoners overseeing the farm's operations.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Monitored prisoners and administered examinations."}],"locations":[{"name":"Erhenrang","aliases":["Capital City","City of Karhide","Arch of the River Gate","New Road and River Port","Island","Genly's Lodgings","Winter","Planet Winter","Gethen","Old Bridge","Ancient Bridge"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"The capital city of Karhide, known for its grand architecture and political significance. A monumental structure completed to enhance Erhenrang's trade and infrastructure. A communal living space for foreigners in Erhenrang, where Genly Ai resides. The icy planet where Karhide is located, with extreme seasonal variations. A historic bridge over the river, noted for its arches and traditional construction methods.","recentEvents":"Hosted a parade celebrating the completion of the Arch of the River Gate, where Genly Ai interacts with key figures like King Argaven XV and Therem Harth rem ir Estraven.; Central to the parade, with the king and masons participating in its final assembly.; Where Genly Ai reflects on his isolation and observes local customs.; Setting for the entire narrative, with Genly Ai navigating its harsh climate and politics.; Mentioned as a reference point for the arch's mortar techniques.","relationships":[{"location":"Royal House","relationship":"Contains the royal residence and administrative center"},{"location":"Palace of Erhenrang","relationship":"Part of the city's walled inner complex"}]},{"name":"Royal House","aliases":["King's Residence","Royal Palace"],"arc":"Estraven's Exile and Cross-National Political Struggles","description":"The fortified palace complex housing the king and key political figures.","recentEvents":"Served as the backdrop for the royal procession and the keystone-laying ceremony.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Central structure within the city"},{"location":"King's House","relationship":"Part of the same complex"}]},{"name":"Corner Red Dwelling","aliases":["Estraven's Home"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"A historic residence of Therem Harth rem ir Estraven, symbolizing his political influence.","recentEvents":"Where Genly Ai is invited for dinner, revealing shifting power dynamics.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Located within the city's walls"}]},{"name":"Sess Embankment","aliases":["River Embankment"],"description":"A public area along the river where crowds gather for events.","recentEvents":"Where the parade crowd watches the keystone ceremony and the king's procession.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Key public space in the city"}],"parentLocation":"Erhenrang"},{"name":"Karhide","aliases":["Nation of Karhide"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Karhide-Orgoreyn Temporal Tensions","description":"A politically complex nation on Winter, ruled by King Argaven XV.","recentEvents":"Central to the narrative, with Genly Ai navigating its social and political structures.","relationships":[{"location":"Winter","relationship":"Nation on the planet"}]},{"name":"North Fall","aliases":["High North Fall"],"description":"A remote, snowbound region bordering Karhide and Orgoreyn, marked by harsh climate and political tension.","recentEvents":"Estraven discusses aiding Karhidish farmers displaced from the Sinoth Valley, risking political fallout with the king.","relationships":[{"location":"Sassinoth Valley","relationship":"Adjacent border region contested by Karhide and Orgoreyn"},{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of Karhide's northern territory"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Sassinoth Valley","aliases":["Sinoth Valley"],"arc":"Estraven's Political Maneuvering and Border Dispute (Historical Context)","description":"A valley trapped in political conflict between Karhide and Orgoreyn, where the narrative's central tensions unfold.","recentEvents":"Karhidish farmers launched a foray here, burning an Orgota village and dumping bodies into the Ey River.","relationships":[{"location":"North Fall","relationship":"Part of the contested border region"},{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Historically inhabited by Orgoreyn settlers"},{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Site of political resistance to the Envoy's mission"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Remny Tower","description":"A tower in Erhenrang where gongs mark the time, symbolizing the city's rigid temporal structure.","recentEvents":"Estraven and Genly Ai hear the gongs signaling midnight as their conversation concludes.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Part of the city's infrastructure"}],"parentLocation":"Erhenrang"},{"name":"Pering Storm-border","aliases":["Storm-border"],"description":"A region in northern Karhide bordering the Pering Ice, known for its harsh climate and the tragic tale of Getheren and Hode.","recentEvents":"The brothers Getheren and Hode vowed kemmering, but their vow was broken after Getheren's brother committed suicide, leading Getheren to flee northward.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Adjacent region"},{"location":"Shath Domain","relationship":"Historical location tied to the brothers' story"}]},{"name":"Pering Ice","aliases":["Pering Glacier"],"description":"A vast glacial sheet covering northern Karhide, contiguous with the Gobrin Ice of Orgoreyn during winter.","recentEvents":"Getheren traveled northward across the Ice, encountering a supernatural realm where the dead dwell.","relationships":[{"location":"Gobrin Ice","relationship":"Contiguous during winter"},{"location":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","relationship":"Site of Getheren's encounter with Hode"}]},{"name":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","aliases":["Blizzard Place"],"description":"A supernatural realm existing within the Pering Ice, where the dead who died in kemmering dwell eternally.","recentEvents":"Getheren met his deceased brother Hode here, who could not speak his name due to his death.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Located within the glacier"},{"location":"Shath Domain","relationship":"Linked to the brothers' tragic history"}],"parentLocation":"Pering Ice"},{"name":"Gobrin Ice","description":"A glacial expanse in Orgoreyn, contiguous with the Pering Ice during winter storms.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a geographical counterpart to the Pering Ice, part of the frozen north.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Contiguous during winter"}]},{"name":"Shath Domain","aliases":["Hearth of Shath"],"description":"A Karhidish domain where the tragic tale of Getheren and Hode originated.","recentEvents":"The brothers' broken vow and Getheren's exile began here, leading to his journey north.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Storm-border","relationship":"Historical location tied to the brothers' story"}]},{"name":"Orgoreyn","aliases":["Karhide's neighbor"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Karhide-Orgoreyn Temporal Tensions","description":"A rival state to Karhide, known for its harsh environment and political tensions.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai contemplates traveling here but hesitates due to potential difficulties returning to Karhide.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Adjacent rival state"}]},{"name":"Fastnesses","arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"A remote eastern region of Karhide containing the Foretellers, who hold significant cultural and prophetic influence.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai resolves to travel here to gather information about Karhide's political dynamics.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Eastern region"}]},{"name":"Grende","aliases":["Grende Region"],"description":"A region in northern Osnoriner, home to Charuthe.","recentEvents":"Herbor travels through the snows of Grende on his way to Charuthe to seek a foretelling for Berosty rem ir Ipe.","relationships":[{"location":"Charuthe","relationship":"Adjacent region"}]},{"name":"New Port","aliases":["New Port"],"description":"A coastal city serving as a departure point for caravans heading east.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai departs from here aboard a trade-caravan bound for the Pering Storm-border.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Storm-border","relationship":"Part of the caravan's route"}]},{"name":"Eskar Pass","aliases":["Eskar Pass"],"description":"A mountain pass through the Kargav range, critical for caravan travel.","recentEvents":"The caravan traverses this pass, encountering extreme weather and avalanches.","relationships":[{"location":"Kargav","relationship":"A key route through the mountain range"}]},{"name":"Ariskostor Fastness","aliases":["Ariskostor Fastness"],"description":"A remote castle-like structure perched on the Kargav's southern face.","recentEvents":"The driver describes it as a residence for the Old Men, inaccessible for most of the year.","relationships":[{"location":"Kargav","relationship":"Located on the mountain range"}]},{"name":"Otherhord","aliases":["Otherhord"],"arc":"Gethenian Cultural Exploration","description":"A secluded Fastness in a forested region, home to the Handdara cult.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai stays here to study the Foretellers' practices and their philosophy of nusuth.","relationships":[{"location":"Fastnesses","relationship":"A specific example of a Handdara retreat"}]},{"name":"Spreve","description":"Domain of the physician from Spreve, a region known for its medical expertise and connection to the Foretellers.","recentEvents":"The physician from Spreve entered the Foretelling circle during the session, interrupting the ritual with a demand for light.","relationships":[{"location":"Otherhord","relationship":"The physician's origin domain"}]},{"name":"Kuseben","aliases":["Kuseben"],"description":"A coastal town in Karhide where Estraven meets Ashe and attempts to flee exile.","recentEvents":"Estraven arrives in Kuseben after fleeing Erhenrang, meets Ashe, and tries to escape to Orgoreyn by sea.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Bordering region; Estraven's escape route"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Shelt Port","aliases":["Shelt"],"description":"A port city in Orgoreyn where Estraven is set ashore after being intercepted by patrol.","recentEvents":"Estraven is rescued by the Kuseben Patrol and landed here, leading to his detention in the Commensal Hospital.","relationships":[{"location":"Charisune Coastal Area Four","relationship":"Adjacent coastal region"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Markets of South Mishnory","aliases":["South Mishnory Markets"],"description":"A bustling market hub in Mishnory where Estraven finds work as a landboat loader.","recentEvents":"Estraven works in the ice-houses and lodges on Fish Island, navigating Orgoreyn's social and political systems.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Central commercial district"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Fish Island","aliases":["Fish Island"],"description":"A crowded island near Mishnory's Markets where Estraven lodges with fellow workers.","recentEvents":"Estraven resides here while working in the ice-houses, enduring harsh conditions and social scrutiny.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Residential district"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Kunderer Embankment","aliases":["Kunderer Embankment"],"description":"A tree-lined area in Mishnory offering respite from the city's heat.","recentEvents":"Estraven retreats here to escape the oppressive summer heat of Mishnory.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Recreational area"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Charisune Coastal Area Four","aliases":["Charisune Coastal Area Four"],"description":"A coastal region in Orgoreyn housing the Commensal Hospital where Estraven is detained.","recentEvents":"Estraven is hospitalized here after a failed escape attempt, where he encounters the Inspector and physician.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Administrative district"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Sennethny","aliases":["Sennethny"],"description":"A location within the Twenty-fourth Commensality of Orgoreyn, tied to Estraven's hospital stay.","recentEvents":"Estraven is registered as a dependent in this commensality after his hospitalization.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Subdivision of the Great Commensality"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Osnoriner","aliases":["Osnoriner Region"],"description":"A region in Karhide known for its unique divorce practices and social customs.","recentEvents":"Discussed as a place where divorce exists but remarriage after divorce or death is prohibited.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of the Karhide region"}]},{"name":"Perunter","aliases":["Perunter Continent"],"description":"An Antarctic continent where incest between generations is reportedly permitted, though disputed.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a possible location with different social norms regarding incest.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Adjacent or nearby region"}]},{"name":"Gorinhering","aliases":["Gorinhering Clan-Hearth"],"description":"A Clan-Hearth on Karhide's Eastern coast, built on a hill above the Hodomin Ocean.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai resided here during the summer, interacting with locals and observing Karhidish culture.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of the Eastern coastal region"},{"location":"Hodomin Ocean","relationship":"Surrounded by the eternal fogs of this ocean"}]},{"name":"Ey River","description":"A glacier-fed border river between Karhide and Orgoreyn, marked by a bridge connecting Passerer and Siuwensin.","recentEvents":"A Karhidish foray raided Siuwensin, prompting Genly's journey into Orgoreyn.","relationships":[{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Karhidish village across the river"},{"location":"Siuwensin","relationship":"Orgota village across the river"}]},{"name":"Passerer","description":"A Karhidish village on the Karhide side of the Ey River bridge.","recentEvents":"A foray from Passerer raids Siuwensin, causing widespread destruction.","relationships":[{"location":"Ey River","relationship":"Located across the river from Siuwensin"},{"location":"Ovord Domain","relationship":"Alleged origin of foray guns"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent Commensal territory"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Siuwensin","arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Orgoreyn Political Tensions","description":"An Orgota village on the Orgoreyn side of the Ey River bridge.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai and refugees are detained here after a raid, interrogated, and held in a storage-barn overnight.","relationships":[{"location":"Ey River","relationship":"Located across the river from Passerer"},{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Source of the raiding foray"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent inspection point"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Commensal Border-Station","description":"An Orgote border checkpoint where Genly obtained a permiso for travel.","recentEvents":"Processed Genly's entry into Orgoreyn after verifying his credentials.","relationships":[{"location":"Siuwensin","relationship":"Adjacent to the Commensal Transient-House"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Ovord Domain","aliases":["Ovord Domain"],"description":"A Commensal region accused of supplying foray guns to Passerer.","recentEvents":"Whispers suggest Ovord Domain's involvement in the Siuwensin raid via foray guns.","relationships":[{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Alleged supplier of foray weapons"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent Commensal territory"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Icefoot Lake","aliases":["Icefoot"],"description":"A frozen lake in Kerm Land where key events unfold.","recentEvents":"Young Estraven falls through the ice, is rescued by Therem of Stok, and later wounded during a hunt.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of Kerm Land"}]},{"name":"Ebos village","description":"A village on the north shore of Icefoot Lake.","recentEvents":"Estraven is taken here after being injured, then later the village sends people to retrieve Estraven's body.","relationships":[{"location":"Icefoot Lake","relationship":"Adjacent"}],"parentLocation":"Icefoot Lake"},{"name":"Rotherer Fastness","description":"A remote fastness where Therem of Stok resides for a year.","recentEvents":"Therem indwells here after being exiled, later returning to Estre as its new lord.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of Kerm Land"}]},{"name":"Artisan School","aliases":["Royal Workshop Foundry"],"description":"A central institution in Karhide where technological and artistic craftsmanship is practiced.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai mentions the ship's components are stored here after landing on Horden Island.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Horden Island","description":"A remote island where Genly Ai first landed on Gethen, serving as a temporary base for his mission.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai's arrival and subsequent departure from the island were discussed during conversations in Mishnory.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Linked via transportation"}]},{"name":"Hall of the Thirty-Three","aliases":["Thirty-Three Hall"],"description":"The assembly chamber where Orgote political debates occur.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai spoke here without public audience; Obsle played a tape of the session for Estraven.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Central political venue"}]},{"name":"Plastics Factory","description":"Estraven's workplace where he produces transparent boxes.","recentEvents":"Estraven works here during the day, reflecting on his exile and the Envoy's mission.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Industrial district"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Central Bureau Radio","description":"The Orgote government's communication hub controlling information flow.","recentEvents":"Estraven notes its role in suppressing news about the Envoy.","relationships":[{"location":"Sarf","relationship":"Operated by the Sarf"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Commensal Public Kemmerhouses","description":"Public venues for communal sexual activities and performances.","recentEvents":"Slose opposes obscene plays here, advocating for moral reform.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Social gathering spaces"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Pyenefen Street","description":"A commercial street where Gaum approaches Estraven.","recentEvents":"Gaum attempts to seduce Estraven, revealing Sarf surveillance.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Urban thoroughfare"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Meshe","aliases":["Center of Time"],"arc":"Gethenian Cultural Exploration","description":"A mystical location central to the narrative's philosophical themes, where Meshe perceives all time and existence simultaneously.","recentEvents":"Meshe's teachings about the Center of Time are recounted, revealing his prophetic visions of past, present, and future events.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Meshe is a spiritual figure associated with Karhide's cosmology"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Tuerresh","description":"A region where the poor man of Sheney discovers a buried treasure, fulfilling Meshe's prophecy.","recentEvents":"The poor man excavates and finds ancient jewels, but Meshe foresees their eventual destruction and his own death.","relationships":[{"location":"Sheney","relationship":"Tuerresh is linked to the village of Sheney through the poor man's journey"}]},{"name":"Ornen Forest","description":"A vast, ancient forest housing a hemmen-tree with a secret leaf hidden in its darkness.","recentEvents":"Meshe plucks the hidden leaf from the tree, symbolizing the revelation of concealed truths.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"The forest is part of Karhide's geography"}]},{"name":"Kundershaden Prison","aliases":["Kundershaden"],"description":"An old, grimy prison in Mishnory used for incarcerating political prisoners.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai was arrested here after being taken from Shusgis' house during a Yomesh festival.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Located within the city"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Pulefen Commensality Third Voluntary Farm & Resettlement Agency","aliases":["Pulefen Farm","Third Voluntary Farm"],"description":"A remote labor camp in Orgoreyn's northwest, surrounded by forest and mountains.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai and other prisoners were transported here after a grueling journey in a caravan-truck.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Located in the extreme northwest"},{"location":"Tarrenpeth Forest","relationship":"Surrounded by this forest"},{"location":"Sembensyens Mountains","relationship":"Bounded by these mountains"}],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Karhide-Orgoreyn Temporal Tensions","parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Sembensyens Mountains","description":"A mountain range in Orgoreyn that the caravan-truck crosses during its journey.","recentEvents":"The truck crossed these mountains at over nine thousand feet during the night.","relationships":[{"location":"Pulefen Farm","relationship":"Boundaries include this mountain range"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Tarrenpeth Forest","description":"A vast, unpopulated coniferous forest in Orgoreyn's northwest, meticulously managed.","recentEvents":"The caravan-truck passed through this forest during its journey to the farm.","relationships":[{"location":"Pulefen Farm","relationship":"Surrounds the farm's perimeter"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Esagel River","description":"A river forming the southern boundary of the Pulefen Farm region in Orgoreyn.","recentEvents":"The Esagel River marks the southern edge of the farm's territory.","relationships":[{"location":"Pulefen Farm","relationship":"Bounded by this river"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"}],"arcs":[{"name":"Genly Ai's Mission and Karhide-Orgoreyn Temporal Tensions","status":"active","characters":["Genly Ai","Weaver Odren","Inspector"],"summary":"Genly's physical deterioration from anti-kemmer hormones and veridicals intensifies, complicating his mission. The Orgote regime's drug examinations and surveillance escalate, threatening his ability to communicate and navigate political tensions between Karhide and Orgoreyn."},{"name":"Estraven's Exile and Cross-National Political Struggles","status":"active","characters":["Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","Commensal Thirty-Three","King Argaven XV"],"summary":"Estraven's clandestine efforts to aid Genly persist, but his political isolation deepens as Orgote factions remain divided, while Genly's arrest underscores the risks of cross-national diplomacy in a climate of surveillance and control."},{"name":"Gethenian Cultural and Sexual Control","status":"active","characters":["Genly Ai","Asra","Weaver Odren"],"summary":"The chapter exposes the Voluntary Farms' systemic suppression of sexual autonomy through drugs, revealing Gethenian society's shift toward enforced passivity. Asra's death and their philosophical dialogues about choice and existence underscore the cultural tension between individual agency and state control."}],"summary":"Genly Ai is arrested in Mishnory and imprisoned in Kundershaden, then transported via a caravan-truck through the Sembensyens Mountains to the Pulefen Farm, a remote labor camp in Orgoreyn. There, he endures harsh conditions with other prisoners, all subjected to drugs suppressing sexual cycles, while the farm's meticulously managed forest and surrounding terrain reflect Orgoreyn's controlled environment."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":17,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Genly Ai","aliases":["Mr. Ai","the Envoy"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"14. The Escape","currentLocation":"Hidden cache in foothills east of Pulefen Farm","description":"The Ekumen's Envoy to Karhide, struggling with the political and psychological complexities of his mission.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Key figure in Genly's mission, later revealed as a political strategist"},{"character":"King Argaven XV","relationship":"The monarch he is attempting to persuade to join the Ekumen"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a tense dialogue with Estraven where Estraven explains his actions to protect Genly from political threats, leading to mutual understanding and a request for mindspeech training."},{"name":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","aliases":["The King’s Ear","Lord Estraven"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"14. The Escape","currentLocation":"Hidden cache in foothills east of Pulefen Farm","description":"A nobleman from the Domain of Estre, known for his complex relationship with Genly Ai and his role in ending the feud between Estre and Stok.","relationships":[{"character":"King Argaven XV","relationship":"Formerly the king's closest confidant and advisor"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Allied through covert communication and financial support"},{"character":"Foreth rem ir Osboth","relationship":"Former kemmering (male companion)"}],"recentEvents":"Revealed his motivations for protecting Genly from political dangers, admitted failure to communicate clearly, and requested to teach Genly mindspeech."},{"name":"King Argaven XV","aliases":["the king"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Royal House","description":"The paranoid and volatile ruler of Karhide, suspicious of foreign influence and internal dissent.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Formerly his most trusted advisor, now exiled"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"The Envoy whose mission he resists and interrogates"}],"recentEvents":"Child's birth and death, political speculation about succession"},{"name":"Pemmer Harge rem ir Tibe","aliases":["the king’s cousin"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The king’s cousin and a member of the upper chamber, known for his rivalry with Estraven.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Rival and political adversary"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Interacted during the dinner conversation"}],"recentEvents":"Featured in news about Karhide’s territorial claims in the Sinoth Valley"},{"name":"servant","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"1. A Parade in Erhenrang","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Karhidish servant who left after the meal.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Departed to their home after the meal, as Karhiders do not employ bonded labor."},{"name":"Getheren","aliases":["Ennoch"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Brother who survived the exile and journey to the Ice, met his brother Hode in the Place Inside the Blizzard.","relationships":[{"character":"Hode","relationship":"Brother"}],"recentEvents":"Traveled to the Pering Ice, encountered Hode, died after returning to Shath and revealing his identity."},{"name":"Hode","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","description":"Getheren's brother who committed suicide after being exiled, now resides in the Place Inside the Blizzard.","relationships":[{"character":"Getheren","relationship":"Brother"}],"recentEvents":"Died by suicide, appeared to Getheren in the Place Inside the Blizzard as a white, lifeless figure."},{"name":"the traveler","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Carried Getheren's message back to Shath, confirming the domain's recovery after Getheren's death.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received Getheren's final message and relayed it to Shath, contributing to the domain's restoration."},{"name":"Lord Berosty rem ir Ipe","aliases":["Ashe Berosty rem ir Ipe"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"4. The Nineteenth Day","currentLocation":"Grende","description":"A nobleman who sought a Foretelling about his death and later killed his kemmering Herbor before dying by suicide.","relationships":[{"character":"Herbor of the Geganner clan","relationship":"kemmering"}],"recentEvents":"Received a Foretelling about his death, killed Herbor, and hanged himself on Odstreth."},{"name":"Herbor of the Geganner clan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"4. The Nineteenth Day","currentLocation":"Grende","description":"A poor man who sought a Foretelling to save his kemmering Berosty rem ir Ipe.","relationships":[{"character":"Lord Berosty rem ir Ipe","relationship":"kemmering"}],"recentEvents":"Sought a Foretelling, was killed by Berosty, and died from the injury."},{"name":"Weaver Odren","aliases":["The Weaver","the Weaver","Faxe"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"13. Down on the Farm","currentLocation":"Pulefen Commensality Third Voluntary Farm & Resettlement Agency","description":"A Foreteller and the Weaver of the group, known for his role in the Foretelling sessions.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Envoy and seeker of answers"},{"character":"the Inspector","relationship":"Aide"}],"recentEvents":"Administered drug examinations to Genly Ai and other prisoners."},{"name":"Goss","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Otherhord","description":"A young Indweller who guides Genly Ai to the Fastness of Otherhord.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Guide and companion"}],"recentEvents":"Led Genly Ai to Otherhord and engaged in conversation about the Handdara"},{"name":"the driver","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"on the caravan","description":"The driver of the landboats guiding the caravan through the Kargav.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Guided the caravan and shared stories about the Fastnesses"},{"name":"the physician from Spreve","aliases":["the physician"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Otherhord","description":"A physician from Spreve who entered the circle during the Foretelling session.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Entered the circle during the Foretelling session, contributing to the disruption of the session."},{"name":"the cook","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"14. The Escape","currentLocation":"Pulefen Commensality Third Voluntary Farm & Resettlement Agency","description":"Guard at Pulefen Farm whose gun was stolen by Estraven.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Had his gun stolen by Estraven during the escape"},{"name":"the fisherman","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"6. One Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A fisherman who initially refused to help Therem","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Refused to assist Therem but later led to his capture"},{"name":"the Inspector","aliases":["Inspector"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"14. The Escape","currentLocation":"Pulefen Commensality Third Voluntary Farm & Resettlement Agency","description":"A government official handling refugee interrogations and border controls.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Overlooked Estraven's escape due to his dothe-induced strength"},{"name":"Commensal Yegey","aliases":["Yegey"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"14. The Escape","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Host at the lunch gathering, curious about the Ekumen.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Maintains dependent relationship"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Host"}],"recentEvents":"Left Mishnor with Obsle, no longer in Genly Ai's trust"},{"name":"Commensal Obsle","aliases":["Obsle"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"14. The Escape","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Commensal with political tensions regarding Estraven","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Politically entangled"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Interrogator"}],"recentEvents":"Left Mishnory with Yegey, no longer in Genly Ai's trust"},{"name":"Foreth rem ir Osboth","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"8. Another Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Orgny Fastness","description":"Estraven's former kemmering, now an Indweller at Orgny Fastness.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Debt owed for aiding Estraven"}],"recentEvents":"Gave Genly Ai money to deliver to Estraven, expressing hope for his survival."},{"name":"the baby","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"8. Another Way into Orgoreyn","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"","relationships":[]},{"name":"Arek of Estre","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The heir of the Domain of Estre, who was killed by a Stok warrior during a feud between the two domains.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Killed by a Stok warrior while traveling through the thore-forest, his body left to be eaten by wild beasts."},{"name":"The murderer","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Stok warrior who killed Arek of Estre during the feud between the domains.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Stabbed Arek of Estre to death and left his body to be eaten by wild beasts."},{"name":"The men from Stok","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A group of Stok warriors who disobeyed their lord's orders and left Arek of Estre's body to be eaten by wild beasts.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Disobeyed their lord's command to bury Arek of Estre, leading to their banishment."},{"name":"Lord Sorve","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The lord of the Domain of Estre who died, leaving his heir Therem to inherit the domain.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Died, leading to Therem becoming Lord of Estre and ending the feud with Stok."},{"name":"The old lord","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Estre","description":"The lord of the Domain of Estre who adopted the child of Arek of Estre as his heir.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Adopted the child of Arek of Estre and named him Therem, who later became Lord of Estre."},{"name":"The people from Ebos village","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"9. Estraven the Traitor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Residents of Ebos village who helped Therem of Stok after he was wounded.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Carried Therem of Stok back to Estre after he was wounded in the thore-forest."},{"name":"Mersen","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Karhidish agent suspected of espionage.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Suspected informant"},{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Suspected of espionage"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed as a spy for Tibe, target of political suspicion"},{"name":"Gaum","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A member of the Sarf who attempted to seduce Estraven during kemmer.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Curious observer"},{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Politically adversarial"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to seduce Estraven during kemmer, failed due to Estraven's abstinence."},{"name":"Humery","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Fat old man in purple, skeptical of interstellar trade.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Expressed disgust at interstellar travel"},{"name":"Slose","aliases":["Commensal Slose"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A Commensal and mystic who interpreted the Envoy's mission as a spiritual event.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Advocate for Ekumen"}],"recentEvents":"Led a committee to suppress obscene plays, interpreted the Envoy's mission as a spiritual event."},{"name":"The fat old man in purple","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Skeptical diner at the lunch gathering.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Expressed disgust at interstellar travel"},{"name":"Csl. Ithepen of the Eynyen District","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A member of the Thirty-Three who proposed inviting the Star Ship to Orgoreyn.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Proposed to Obsle to invite the Star Ship to Orgoreyn, but the plan was rejected."},{"name":"Alshel","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Presiding officer in the Hall of the Thirty-Three during the Envoy's speech.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Presided over the session where the Envoy spoke about the Star Ship."},{"name":"Kaharosile","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"11. Soliloquies in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"A member of the Domination faction who interrupted the Envoy's speech with accusations.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Interrupted the session with accusations against the Envoy, claiming he was a Karhidish agent."},{"name":"Meshe","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"12. On Time and Darkness","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A High Priest whose sayings form the Yomesh Canon, central to the philosophical and cosmological teachings of Gethen.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Delivered teachings on time, darkness, and the nature of existence through parables and prophecies."},{"name":"Tuhulme","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"12. On Time and Darkness","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The author of the Sayings attributed to Meshe, a figure in Gethen's religious and philosophical history.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Compiled the Sayings of Meshe into the Yomesh Canon."},{"name":"The poor man of Sheney","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"12. On Time and Darkness","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A character in a parable about seeking treasure and the consequences of greed.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Discovered a buried treasure but faced a grim fate foretold by Meshe."},{"name":"The Lord of Shorth","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"12. On Time and Darkness","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A ruler referenced in Meshe's parable about the nature of time and vision.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Mentioned in Meshe's mystical vision of the universe's expansion."},{"name":"the old man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"13. Down on the Farm","currentLocation":"Pulefen Commensality Third Voluntary Farm & Resettlement Agency","description":"A prisoner in the caravan truck recognized for being least resistant to cold.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Lived in the dormitory with Genly Ai and the man with a bad cough."},{"name":"the man with a bad cough","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"13. Down on the Farm","currentLocation":"Pulefen Commensality Third Voluntary Farm & Resettlement Agency","description":"A prisoner in the caravan truck recognized for being least resistant to cold.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Survived the caravan journey and was assigned to the farm labor camp."},{"name":"the girl","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"13. Down on the Farm","currentLocation":"Pulefen Commensality Third Voluntary Farm & Resettlement Agency","description":"An Orgota woman in kemmer who approached Genly Ai during the caravan journey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Attempted to seek solace from Genly Ai during the caravan journey."},{"name":"Asra","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"13. Down on the Farm","currentLocation":"Pulefen Commensality Third Voluntary Farm & Resettlement Agency","description":"A former carpenter imprisoned at the farm, known for his storytelling and eventual death from illness.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Prisoner companion"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in conversations with Genly Ai about his past, died after falling into a coma."},{"name":"the guards","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"13. Down on the Farm","currentLocation":"Pulefen Commensality Third Voluntary Farm & Resettlement Agency","description":"Probationary prisoners overseeing the farm's operations.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Monitored prisoners and administered examinations."},{"name":"Commissioner Shusgis","aliases":["Shusgis"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"10. Conversations in Mishnory","currentLocation":"Mishnory","description":"Coerced into providing information about the Sarf by Genly Ai.","relationships":[{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Provided information about Sarf and political factions"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed Orgoreyn's secret police, Estraven's status, and political factions"},{"name":"Sardon rem ir Chene-wich","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"14. The Escape","currentLocation":"Royal Embassy","description":"Former court acquaintance who conveyed a message to King Argaven.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Helped Genly Ai communicate with King Argaven"},{"name":"Mavriva","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"14. The Escape","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Old man who led the hunting party in the Esagel region.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Guided Estraven's escape route through the wilderness"},{"name":"the skiers","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"14. The Escape","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Skiers encountered by Estraven during his escape.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Briefly interacted with Estraven before continuing their journey"}],"locations":[{"name":"Erhenrang","aliases":["Capital City","City of Karhide","Arch of the River Gate","New Road and River Port","Island","Genly's Lodgings","Winter","Planet Winter","Gethen","Old Bridge","Ancient Bridge"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"The capital city of Karhide, known for its grand architecture and political significance. A monumental structure completed to enhance Erhenrang's trade and infrastructure. A communal living space for foreigners in Erhenrang, where Genly Ai resides. The icy planet where Karhide is located, with extreme seasonal variations. A historic bridge over the river, noted for its arches and traditional construction methods.","recentEvents":"Hosted a parade celebrating the completion of the Arch of the River Gate, where Genly Ai interacts with key figures like King Argaven XV and Therem Harth rem ir Estraven.; Central to the parade, with the king and masons participating in its final assembly.; Where Genly Ai reflects on his isolation and observes local customs.; Setting for the entire narrative, with Genly Ai navigating its harsh climate and politics.; Mentioned as a reference point for the arch's mortar techniques.","relationships":[{"location":"Royal House","relationship":"Contains the royal residence and administrative center"},{"location":"Palace of Erhenrang","relationship":"Part of the city's walled inner complex"}]},{"name":"Royal House","aliases":["King's Residence","Royal Palace"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Karhide-Orgoreyn Temporal Tensions","description":"The fortified palace complex housing the king and key political figures.","recentEvents":"Served as the backdrop for the royal procession and the keystone-laying ceremony.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Central structure within the city"},{"location":"King's House","relationship":"Part of the same complex"}]},{"name":"Corner Red Dwelling","aliases":["Estraven's Home"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"A historic residence of Therem Harth rem ir Estraven, symbolizing his political influence.","recentEvents":"Where Genly Ai is invited for dinner, revealing shifting power dynamics.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Located within the city's walls"}]},{"name":"Sess Embankment","aliases":["River Embankment"],"description":"A public area along the river where crowds gather for events.","recentEvents":"Where the parade crowd watches the keystone ceremony and the king's procession.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Key public space in the city"}],"parentLocation":"Erhenrang"},{"name":"Karhide","aliases":["Nation of Karhide"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Estraven's Political Protection","description":"A politically complex nation on Winter, ruled by King Argaven XV.","recentEvents":"Central to the narrative, with Genly Ai navigating its social and political structures.","relationships":[{"location":"Winter","relationship":"Nation on the planet"}]},{"name":"North Fall","aliases":["High North Fall"],"description":"A remote, snowbound region bordering Karhide and Orgoreyn, marked by harsh climate and political tension.","recentEvents":"Estraven discusses aiding Karhidish farmers displaced from the Sinoth Valley, risking political fallout with the king.","relationships":[{"location":"Sassinoth Valley","relationship":"Adjacent border region contested by Karhide and Orgoreyn"},{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of Karhide's northern territory"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Sassinoth Valley","aliases":["Sinoth Valley"],"arc":"Estraven's Political Maneuvering and Border Dispute (Historical Context)","description":"A valley trapped in political conflict between Karhide and Orgoreyn, where the narrative's central tensions unfold.","recentEvents":"Karhidish farmers launched a foray here, burning an Orgota village and dumping bodies into the Ey River.","relationships":[{"location":"North Fall","relationship":"Part of the contested border region"},{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Historically inhabited by Orgoreyn settlers"},{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Site of political resistance to the Envoy's mission"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Remny Tower","description":"A tower in Erhenrang where gongs mark the time, symbolizing the city's rigid temporal structure.","recentEvents":"Estraven and Genly Ai hear the gongs signaling midnight as their conversation concludes.","relationships":[{"location":"Erhenrang","relationship":"Part of the city's infrastructure"}],"parentLocation":"Erhenrang"},{"name":"Pering Storm-border","aliases":["Storm-border"],"description":"A region in northern Karhide bordering the Pering Ice, known for its harsh climate and the tragic tale of Getheren and Hode.","recentEvents":"The brothers Getheren and Hode vowed kemmering, but their vow was broken after Getheren's brother committed suicide, leading Getheren to flee northward.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Adjacent region"},{"location":"Shath Domain","relationship":"Historical location tied to the brothers' story"}]},{"name":"Pering Ice","aliases":["Pering Glacier"],"description":"A vast glacial sheet covering northern Karhide, contiguous with the Gobrin Ice of Orgoreyn during winter.","recentEvents":"Getheren traveled northward across the Ice, encountering a supernatural realm where the dead dwell.","relationships":[{"location":"Gobrin Ice","relationship":"Contiguous during winter"},{"location":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","relationship":"Site of Getheren's encounter with Hode"}]},{"name":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","aliases":["Blizzard Place"],"description":"A supernatural realm existing within the Pering Ice, where the dead who died in kemmering dwell eternally.","recentEvents":"Getheren met his deceased brother Hode here, who could not speak his name due to his death.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Located within the glacier"},{"location":"Shath Domain","relationship":"Linked to the brothers' tragic history"}],"parentLocation":"Pering Ice"},{"name":"Gobrin Ice","description":"A glacial expanse in Orgoreyn, contiguous with the Pering Ice during winter storms.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a geographical counterpart to the Pering Ice, part of the frozen north.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Ice","relationship":"Contiguous during winter"}]},{"name":"Shath Domain","aliases":["Hearth of Shath"],"description":"A Karhidish domain where the tragic tale of Getheren and Hode originated.","recentEvents":"The brothers' broken vow and Getheren's exile began here, leading to his journey north.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Storm-border","relationship":"Historical location tied to the brothers' story"}]},{"name":"Orgoreyn","aliases":["Karhide's neighbor","Orgny Fastness"],"arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Estraven's Political Protection","description":"The cold, politically volatile planet where Genly Ai and Estraven navigate power struggles between Karhide and Orgoreyn.","recentEvents":"Estraven recounts his role in orchestrating Genly's exile to Orgoreyn to protect him from assassination by Pemmer Harge rem ir Tibe.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Adjacent rival state"},{"location":"Pulefen Commensality Third Voluntary Farm & Resettlement Agency","relationship":"Target of political intrigue due to its role in Genly's hidden refuge"}]},{"name":"Fastnesses","arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Political Intrigue","description":"A remote eastern region of Karhide containing the Foretellers, who hold significant cultural and prophetic influence.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai resolves to travel here to gather information about Karhide's political dynamics.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Eastern region"}]},{"name":"Grende","aliases":["Grende Region"],"description":"A region in northern Osnoriner, home to Charuthe.","recentEvents":"Herbor travels through the snows of Grende on his way to Charuthe to seek a foretelling for Berosty rem ir Ipe.","relationships":[{"location":"Charuthe","relationship":"Adjacent region"}]},{"name":"New Port","aliases":["New Port"],"description":"A coastal city serving as a departure point for caravans heading east.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai departs from here aboard a trade-caravan bound for the Pering Storm-border.","relationships":[{"location":"Pering Storm-border","relationship":"Part of the caravan's route"}]},{"name":"Eskar Pass","aliases":["Eskar Pass"],"description":"A mountain pass through the Kargav range, critical for caravan travel.","recentEvents":"The caravan traverses this pass, encountering extreme weather and avalanches.","relationships":[{"location":"Kargav","relationship":"A key route through the mountain range"}]},{"name":"Ariskostor Fastness","aliases":["Ariskostor Fastness"],"description":"A remote castle-like structure perched on the Kargav's southern face.","recentEvents":"The driver describes it as a residence for the Old Men, inaccessible for most of the year.","relationships":[{"location":"Kargav","relationship":"Located on the mountain range"}]},{"name":"Otherhord","aliases":["Otherhord"],"arc":"Gethenian Cultural Exploration","description":"A secluded Fastness in a forested region, home to the Handdara cult.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai stays here to study the Foretellers' practices and their philosophy of nusuth.","relationships":[{"location":"Fastnesses","relationship":"A specific example of a Handdara retreat"}]},{"name":"Spreve","description":"Domain of the physician from Spreve, a region known for its medical expertise and connection to the Foretellers.","recentEvents":"The physician from Spreve entered the Foretelling circle during the session, interrupting the ritual with a demand for light.","relationships":[{"location":"Otherhord","relationship":"The physician's origin domain"}]},{"name":"Kuseben","aliases":["Kuseben"],"description":"A coastal town in Karhide where Estraven meets Ashe and attempts to flee exile.","recentEvents":"Estraven arrives in Kuseben after fleeing Erhenrang, meets Ashe, and tries to escape to Orgoreyn by sea.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Bordering region; Estraven's escape route"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Shelt Port","aliases":["Shelt"],"description":"A port city in Orgoreyn where Estraven is set ashore after being intercepted by patrol.","recentEvents":"Estraven is rescued by the Kuseben Patrol and landed here, leading to his detention in the Commensal Hospital.","relationships":[{"location":"Charisune Coastal Area Four","relationship":"Adjacent coastal region"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Markets of South Mishnory","aliases":["South Mishnory Markets"],"description":"A bustling market hub in Mishnory where Estraven finds work as a landboat loader.","recentEvents":"Estraven works in the ice-houses and lodges on Fish Island, navigating Orgoreyn's social and political systems.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Central commercial district"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Fish Island","aliases":["Fish Island"],"description":"A crowded island near Mishnory's Markets where Estraven lodges with fellow workers.","recentEvents":"Estraven resides here while working in the ice-houses, enduring harsh conditions and social scrutiny.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Residential district"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Kunderer Embankment","aliases":["Kunderer Embankment"],"description":"A tree-lined area in Mishnory offering respite from the city's heat.","recentEvents":"Estraven retreats here to escape the oppressive summer heat of Mishnory.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Recreational area"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Charisune Coastal Area Four","aliases":["Charisune Coastal Area Four"],"description":"A coastal region in Orgoreyn housing the Commensal Hospital where Estraven is detained.","recentEvents":"Estraven is hospitalized here after a failed escape attempt, where he encounters the Inspector and physician.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Administrative district"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Sennethny","aliases":["Sennethny"],"description":"A location within the Twenty-fourth Commensality of Orgoreyn, tied to Estraven's hospital stay.","recentEvents":"Estraven is registered as a dependent in this commensality after his hospitalization.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Subdivision of the Great Commensality"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Osnoriner","aliases":["Osnoriner Region"],"description":"A region in Karhide known for its unique divorce practices and social customs.","recentEvents":"Discussed as a place where divorce exists but remarriage after divorce or death is prohibited.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of the Karhide region"}]},{"name":"Perunter","aliases":["Perunter Continent"],"description":"An Antarctic continent where incest between generations is reportedly permitted, though disputed.","recentEvents":"Mentioned as a possible location with different social norms regarding incest.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Adjacent or nearby region"}]},{"name":"Gorinhering","aliases":["Gorinhering Clan-Hearth"],"description":"A Clan-Hearth on Karhide's Eastern coast, built on a hill above the Hodomin Ocean.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai resided here during the summer, interacting with locals and observing Karhidish culture.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of the Eastern coastal region"},{"location":"Hodomin Ocean","relationship":"Surrounded by the eternal fogs of this ocean"}]},{"name":"Ey River","description":"A glacier-fed border river between Karhide and Orgoreyn, marked by a bridge connecting Passerer and Siuwensin.","recentEvents":"A Karhidish foray raided Siuwensin, prompting Genly's journey into Orgoreyn.","relationships":[{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Karhidish village across the river"},{"location":"Siuwensin","relationship":"Orgota village across the river"}]},{"name":"Passerer","description":"A Karhidish village on the Karhide side of the Ey River bridge.","recentEvents":"A foray from Passerer raids Siuwensin, causing widespread destruction.","relationships":[{"location":"Ey River","relationship":"Located across the river from Siuwensin"},{"location":"Ovord Domain","relationship":"Alleged origin of foray guns"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent Commensal territory"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Siuwensin","arc":"Genly Ai's Mission and Orgoreyn Political Tensions","description":"An Orgota village on the Orgoreyn side of the Ey River bridge.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai and refugees are detained here after a raid, interrogated, and held in a storage-barn overnight.","relationships":[{"location":"Ey River","relationship":"Located across the river from Passerer"},{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Source of the raiding foray"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent inspection point"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Commensal Border-Station","description":"An Orgote border checkpoint where Genly obtained a permiso for travel.","recentEvents":"Processed Genly's entry into Orgoreyn after verifying his credentials.","relationships":[{"location":"Siuwensin","relationship":"Adjacent to the Commensal Transient-House"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Ovord Domain","aliases":["Ovord Domain"],"description":"A Commensal region accused of supplying foray guns to Passerer.","recentEvents":"Whispers suggest Ovord Domain's involvement in the Siuwensin raid via foray guns.","relationships":[{"location":"Passerer","relationship":"Alleged supplier of foray weapons"},{"location":"Commensal Border-Station","relationship":"Adjacent Commensal territory"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Icefoot Lake","aliases":["Icefoot"],"description":"A frozen lake in Kerm Land where key events unfold.","recentEvents":"Young Estraven falls through the ice, is rescued by Therem of Stok, and later wounded during a hunt.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of Kerm Land"}]},{"name":"Ebos village","description":"A village on the north shore of Icefoot Lake.","recentEvents":"Estraven is taken here after being injured, then later the village sends people to retrieve Estraven's body.","relationships":[{"location":"Icefoot Lake","relationship":"Adjacent"}],"parentLocation":"Icefoot Lake"},{"name":"Rotherer Fastness","description":"A remote fastness where Therem of Stok resides for a year.","recentEvents":"Therem indwells here after being exiled, later returning to Estre as its new lord.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Part of Kerm Land"}]},{"name":"Artisan School","aliases":["Royal Workshop Foundry"],"description":"A central institution in Karhide where technological and artistic craftsmanship is practiced.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai mentions the ship's components are stored here after landing on Horden Island.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Horden Island","description":"A remote island where Genly Ai first landed on Gethen, serving as a temporary base for his mission.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai's arrival and subsequent departure from the island were discussed during conversations in Mishnory.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Linked via transportation"}]},{"name":"Hall of the Thirty-Three","aliases":["Thirty-Three Hall"],"description":"The assembly chamber where Orgote political debates occur.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai spoke here without public audience; Obsle played a tape of the session for Estraven.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Central political venue"}]},{"name":"Plastics Factory","description":"Estraven's workplace where he produces transparent boxes.","recentEvents":"Estraven works here during the day, reflecting on his exile and the Envoy's mission.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Industrial district"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Central Bureau Radio","description":"The Orgote government's communication hub controlling information flow.","recentEvents":"Estraven notes its role in suppressing news about the Envoy.","relationships":[{"location":"Sarf","relationship":"Operated by the Sarf"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Commensal Public Kemmerhouses","description":"Public venues for communal sexual activities and performances.","recentEvents":"Slose opposes obscene plays here, advocating for moral reform.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Social gathering spaces"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Pyenefen Street","description":"A commercial street where Gaum approaches Estraven.","recentEvents":"Gaum attempts to seduce Estraven, revealing Sarf surveillance.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Urban thoroughfare"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Meshe","aliases":["Center of Time"],"arc":"Gethenian Cultural Exploration","description":"A mystical location central to the narrative's philosophical themes, where Meshe perceives all time and existence simultaneously.","recentEvents":"Meshe's teachings about the Center of Time are recounted, revealing his prophetic visions of past, present, and future events.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"Meshe is a spiritual figure associated with Karhide's cosmology"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Tuerresh","description":"A region where the poor man of Sheney discovers a buried treasure, fulfilling Meshe's prophecy.","recentEvents":"The poor man excavates and finds ancient jewels, but Meshe foresees their eventual destruction and his own death.","relationships":[{"location":"Sheney","relationship":"Tuerresh is linked to the village of Sheney through the poor man's journey"}]},{"name":"Ornen Forest","description":"A vast, ancient forest housing a hemmen-tree with a secret leaf hidden in its darkness.","recentEvents":"Meshe plucks the hidden leaf from the tree, symbolizing the revelation of concealed truths.","relationships":[{"location":"Karhide","relationship":"The forest is part of Karhide's geography"}]},{"name":"Kundershaden Prison","aliases":["Kundershaden"],"description":"An old, grimy prison in Mishnory used for incarcerating political prisoners.","recentEvents":"Genly Ai was arrested here after being taken from Shusgis' house during a Yomesh festival.","relationships":[{"location":"Mishnory","relationship":"Located within the city"}],"parentLocation":"Karhide"},{"name":"Pulefen Commensality Third Voluntary Farm & Resettlement Agency","aliases":["Pulefen Farm","Third Voluntary Farm"],"arc":"Gethenian Cultural and Sexual Control","description":"A resettlement colony where Genly Ai and Estraven hide after escaping Karhide's political dangers.","recentEvents":"Genly and Estraven confront the consequences of Estraven's covert actions to safeguard Genly's mission.","relationships":[{"location":"Orgoreyn","relationship":"Site of Genly's temporary refuge and political maneuvering"},{"location":"Tarrenpeth Forest","relationship":"Surrounded by this forest"},{"location":"Sembensyens Mountains","relationship":"Bounded by these mountains"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Sembensyens Mountains","description":"A mountain range in Orgoreyn that the caravan-truck crosses during its journey.","recentEvents":"The truck crossed these mountains at over nine thousand feet during the night.","relationships":[{"location":"Pulefen Farm","relationship":"Boundaries include this mountain range"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Tarrenpeth Forest","description":"A vast, unpopulated coniferous forest in Orgoreyn's northwest, meticulously managed.","recentEvents":"The caravan-truck passed through this forest during its journey to the farm.","relationships":[{"location":"Pulefen Farm","relationship":"Surrounds the farm's perimeter"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Esagel River","description":"A river forming the southern boundary of the Pulefen Farm region in Orgoreyn.","recentEvents":"The Esagel River marks the southern edge of the farm's territory.","relationships":[{"location":"Pulefen Farm","relationship":"Bounded by this river"}],"parentLocation":"Orgoreyn"},{"name":"Ethwen","aliases":["Esagel Bay Port"],"description":"A gray port city built on the rocky shores of Esagel Bay, known for its rainy climate and seafaring population.","recentEvents":"The narrator buys trapping equipment and obtains a hunter's license here, planning to travel north.","relationships":[{"location":"Esagel River","relationship":"Located at the mouth of the river"},{"location":"Pulefen Commensality Third Voluntary Farm & Resettlement Agency","relationship":"Destination for the narrator's journey"}]},{"name":"Turuf","description":"A town along the Esagel River where the narrator temporarily resides and caches supplies.","recentEvents":"The narrator leaves the hunting party here, caches equipment, and returns to prepare for his escape.","relationships":[{"location":"Esagel River","relationship":"Located along the river's banks"},{"location":"Pulefen Farm","relationship":"Southward direction from the farm"}]},{"name":"Commensal Bureau","description":"An administrative office responsible for issuing licenses and permits for voluntary farms and trapping activities.","recentEvents":"The narrator acquires a hunter's license and authorization documents here.","relationships":[{"location":"Pulefen Commensality Third Voluntary Farm & Resettlement Agency","relationship":"Regulatory authority for the farm"}]},{"name":"Fire-Hills","aliases":["Fire Mountains"],"description":"A distant range of volcanic peaks known for their smoky plumes, located far to the north of Orgoreyn.","recentEvents":"Smoke from Udenushreke is observed, marking the narrator's approach to the region.","relationships":[{"location":"Udenushreke","relationship":"Part of the Fire-Hills range"}]},{"name":"Udenushreke","aliases":["Fire-Hill"],"description":"A specific volcanic peak within the Fire-Hills range, known for its persistent smoke and distant visibility.","recentEvents":"Smoke from this fire-hill is seen by the narrator during his journey north.","relationships":[{"location":"Fire-Hills","relationship":"A prominent feature of the range"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Genly Ai's Mission and Estraven's Political Protection","status":"active","characters":["Genly Ai","Therem Harth rem ir Estraven"],"summary":"Estraven successfully rescues Genly from Pulefen Farm using dothe-induced strength, but Genly remains vulnerable to the Farm's drug regimen and the political tensions between Karhide and Orgoreyn persist."},{"name":"Estraven's Exile and Cross-National Political Strategies","status":"active","characters":["Therem Harth rem ir Estraven"],"summary":"Estraven's escape from Pulefen Farm and covert aid to Genly escalate his political risks, as the Sarf faction now hunts him, while his alliance with Karhide's nobles remains precarious."},{"name":"Gethenian Cultural and Sexual Control","status":"active","characters":["Genly Ai","Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","Weaver Odren","Commensal Yegey"],"summary":"Genly's physical and psychological trauma from the Farm's drugs persists, while Estraven's knowledge of the Handdara challenges the regime's narrative, highlighting systemic control and the cultural tensions around kemmering."},{"name":"Genly Ai's Mission and Karhide-Orgoreyn Temporal Tensions","status":"active","characters":["Genly Ai","Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","King Argaven XV","Pemmer Harge rem ir Tibe"],"summary":"Estraven reveals his strategic manipulation of Karhide's political landscape to protect Genly, exposing the Thirty-Three Commensals' failure to act and their role in Genly's capture. Genly remains in Pulefen Farm, while Estraven is in Orgoreyn, with unresolved tensions between the two nations."},{"name":"Estraven's Exile and Cross-National Political Struggles","status":"active","characters":["Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","King Argaven XV","Sarf faction","Thirty-Three Commensals"],"summary":"Estraven's exile escalates as he navigates Orgoreyn's political landscape, revealing his covert efforts to secure Genly's safety and the ongoing power struggles between Karhide, Orgoreyn, and the Sarf faction."}],"summary":"Genly Ai and Estraven reconcile after a tense confrontation, with Estraven explaining his covert efforts to protect Genly from political assassination. Their dialogue reveals the complex alliances and betrayals shaping Gethen's power dynamics, culminating in a plan to use mindspeech to bridge their mistrust. The narrative now focuses on their shared goal of uniting Karhide and Orgoreyn despite political fractures."},"model":"qwen3:8b","appVersion":"0.1.0"},{"index":18,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Genly Ai","aliases":["Mr. Ai","the Envoy"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"15. To the Ice","currentLocation":"On the Ice, traveling through the forest towards the glacier","description":"The Ekumen's Envoy to Karhide, struggling with the political and psychological complexities of his mission.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Key figure in Genly's mission, later revealed as a political strategist"},{"character":"King Argaven XV","relationship":"The monarch he is attempting to persuade to join the Ekumen"}],"recentEvents":"Planned the glacier crossing route, discussed survival strategies, and prepared supplies for the journey"},{"name":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","aliases":["The King’s Ear","Lord Estraven"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"15. To the Ice","currentLocation":"On the Ice, traveling through the forest towards the glacier","description":"A nobleman from the Domain of Estre, known for his complex relationship with Genly Ai and his role in ending the feud between Estre and Stok.","relationships":[{"character":"King Argaven XV","relationship":"Formerly the king's closest confidant and advisor"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Allied through covert communication and financial support"},{"character":"Foreth rem ir Osboth","relationship":"Former kemmering (male companion)"}],"recentEvents":"Set traps for pesthry, provided sustenance for the journey, managed their sledge through extreme weather, and guided them toward the Gobrin Glacier."},{"name":"King Argaven XV","aliases":["the king"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Royal House","description":"The paranoid and volatile ruler of Karhide, suspicious of foreign influence and internal dissent.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Formerly his most trusted advisor, now exiled"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"The Envoy whose mission he resists and interrogates"}],"recentEvents":"Child's birth and death, political speculation about succession"},{"name":"Pemmer Harge rem ir Tibe","aliases":["the king’s cousin"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"5. The Domestication of Hunch","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The king’s cousin and a member of the upper chamber, known for his rivalry with Estraven.","relationships":[{"character":"Therem Harth rem ir Estraven","relationship":"Rival and political adversary"},{"character":"Genly Ai","relationship":"Interacted during the dinner conversation"}],"recentEvents":"Featured in news about Karhide’s territorial claims in the Sinoth Valley"},{"name":"servant","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"1. A Parade in Erhenrang","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Karhidish servant who left after the meal.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Departed to their home after the meal, as Karhiders do not employ bonded labor."},{"name":"Getheren","aliases":["Ennoch"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Brother who survived the exile and journey to the Ice, met his brother Hode in the Place Inside the Blizzard.","relationships":[{"character":"Hode","relationship":"Brother"}],"recentEvents":"Traveled to the Pering Ice, encountered Hode, died after returning to Shath and revealing his identity."},{"name":"Hode","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"The Place Inside the Blizzard","description":"Getheren's brother who committed suicide after being exiled, now resides in the Place Inside the Blizzard.","relationships":[{"character":"Getheren","relationship":"Brother"}],"recentEvents":"Died by suicide, appeared to Getheren in the Place Inside the Blizzard as a white, lifeless figure."},{"name":"the traveler","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"2. The Place Inside the Blizzard","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Carried Getheren's message back to Shath, confirming the domain's recovery after Getheren's death.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Received Getheren's final message and relayed it to Shath, contributing to the domain's restoration."},{"name":"Lord Berosty rem ir Ipe","aliases":["Ashe Berosty rem ir Ipe"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"4. The Nineteenth Day","currentLocation":"Grende","description":"A nobleman who sought a Foretelling about his death and later killed his kemmering Herbor before dying by suicide.","relationships":[{"character":"Herbor of the Geganner clan","relationship":"kemmering"}],"recentEvents":"Received a Foretelling about his death, killed Herbor, and hanged himself on Odstreth."},{"name":"Herbor of the Geganner clan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"4. The Nineteenth Day","currentLocation":"Grende","description":"A poor man who sought a Foretelling to save his kemmering Berosty rem ir Ipe.","relationships":[{"character":"Lord Berosty rem ir Ipe","relationship":"kemmering"}],"recentEvents":"Sought a Foretelling, was killed by Berosty, and died from the injury."},{"name":"Weaver Odren","aliases":["The Weaver","the Weaver","Faxe"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"13. Down on the Farm","currentLocation":"Pulefen Commensality Third Voluntary Farm & Resettlement Agency","description":"A Foreteller and the Weaver of the g